(1, 1, 0, 0, 'The Verb \"To Be\"', 'one', 'The verb [i]to be[/i] describes the identity, qualities, or condition of a person or object.  Use the following to form the present tense of the verb to be:\r\n\r\nI	am	happy.\r\nYou	are	smart.\r\nHe	is	short.\r\nShe	is	busy.\r\nIt	is	tall.\r\nWe	are	tired.\r\nThey	are	here.', NULL, 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 05:30:44', '2019-07-13 06:12:30'),
(2, 1, 1, 4, 'The Most Common Verb: \'To Be\'', 'the-verb--to-be-', 'Introduction to the verb \'To Be\' .', '<p>The verb <strong>To Be</strong>&nbsp;describes the identity, qualities, or condition of a person or object.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Use the following to form the present tense of the verb <strong>To Be:<br /></strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n<table class=\"table lesson-table\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Subject</th>\r\n<th>Verb</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I</td>\r\n<td>am</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>You</td>\r\n<td>are</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>He, She, It</td>\r\n<td>is</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>We</td>\r\n<td>are</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>They</td>\r\n<td>are</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Here are some example sentences using <strong>To Be</strong>:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>I <strong>am</strong> happy.</p>\r\n<p>You <strong>are</strong> smart.</p>\r\n<p>He <strong>is</strong> tall.</p>\r\n<p>She <strong>is</strong> busy.</p>\r\n<p>It <strong>is</strong> purple.</p>\r\n<p>We <strong>are</strong> tired.</p>\r\n<p>They <strong>are</strong> young.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>For regular nouns, the verb form depends on whether the subject is singular (one) or plural (more than one):</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n<table class=\"table lesson-table\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Subject</th>\r\n<th>Verb</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Singular</td>\r\n<td>is</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Plural</td>\r\n<td>are</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>The car <strong>is</strong> red. <strong>&rarr; </strong>Singular, one car</p>\r\n<p>The cars <strong>are</strong> fast. <strong>&rarr; </strong>Plural, more than one car</p>\r\n<p>Here are more examples with singular and plural subjects:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>The tree <strong>is</strong> green.&nbsp; (one tree)</p>\r\n<p>The clouds <strong>are</strong> white.&nbsp; (more than one cloud)</p>\r\n<p>The sky <strong>is</strong> blue.&nbsp; (one sky)</p>\r\n<p>The cows <strong>are</strong> brown.&nbsp; (more than one cow)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-note\">\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> In some languages there is more than one verb for <strong>To Be</strong> but in English there is only one.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Summary</h3>\r\n<p>Most verbs are used for actions but the verb <strong>To Be</strong> describes conditions.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 06:13:24', '2019-07-17 08:35:56'),
(3, 1, 1, 2, 'The Basic Structure', 'introduction', 'This lesson describes the basic structure of the English language.', '<p>A basic sentence looks like this:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Clouds are white.</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Clouds</strong> is the <strong>subject</strong>. Subjects are usually nouns. Nouns are people, places, and things.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Are</strong> is the <strong>verb</strong> (the verb is <strong>To Be</strong>) Verbs describe an action or condition.</p>\r\n<p><strong>White</strong> is the <strong>adjective</strong>. Adjective describes the noun.</p>\r\n<p>Here are more examples:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>The sky is blue.</p>\r\n<p>The tree is tall.</p>\r\n<p>The sheep is hungry.</p>\r\n<p>He is young.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Summary</h3>\r\n<p>The word order in a basic sentence is:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Subject/Noun &rarr; Verb &rarr; Adjective</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Nouns</strong> are people, places, and things.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Verbs</strong> are actions or conditions.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Adjectives</strong> describe nouns.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 07:25:36', '2019-07-17 06:38:51'),
(4, 2, 2, 1, 'Frases Avanzadas en Español 1', 'new-vocabulary', 'El último vocabulario avanzado en español', '<p>Fuera de contacto - ex. Fuera de contacto con la realidad.</p>\r\n<p>Volcado de datos - descarga de datos</p>\r\n<p>Sonado - Emitir [una cosa] alg&uacute;n sonido o ruido.&nbsp; hecho, acontecimiento. Que es muy conocido y tiene mucha repercusi&oacute;n social.</p>\r\n<p>bot&iacute;n - bot&iacute;n pirata</p>\r\n<p>Grieta - El terremoto de California cre&oacute; una grieta gigante en la tierra.</p>\r\n<p>Hedor - Los vecinos avisaron a la Polic&iacute;a de un fuerte hedor que proven&iacute;a de la vivienda.</p>\r\n<p>Paliza - Serie numerosa de golpes dados a una persona como castigo o con la intenci&oacute;n de hacerle da&ntilde;o.</p>\r\n<p>Tarrina - tina; tina de manteca</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 08:05:42', '2019-07-27 20:02:17'),
(5, 1, 1, 3, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', 'To begin, please look up these words in your native language and add them to your vocabulary list.\r\n\r\nThis step requires that you create an account so that your vocabulary list can be saved.  Click here to register your account', NULL, 1, 20, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 11:39:16', '2019-08-02 08:57:18'),
(286, 3, 4, 0, 'Sample English Lessons', 'sample-english-lessons', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-08-04 01:15:57', '2019-08-04 01:35:27'),
(289, 3, 4, 2, 'Do we have time?', 'do-we-have-time-', NULL, '<h3>PRESENT</h3>\r\n<p>Do we have food?</p>\r\n<p>Yes, we have food.</p>\r\n<p>Does he have food?</p>\r\n<p>No, he doesn\'t have food.</p>\r\n<p>Do you have food?</p>\r\n<p>No, I do not have food.</p>\r\n<h3>FUTURE</h3>\r\n<p>Will we have food?</p>\r\n<p>Yes, we will have food.</p>\r\n<p>Will he have food?</p>\r\n<p>No, he will not have food.</p>\r\n<p>Will you have food?</p>\r\n<p>No, I won\'t have food.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-08-04 01:34:33', '2019-08-04 01:38:41'),
(287, 3, 4, 1, 'Do you see the bird?', 'do-you-see-the-bird-', NULL, '<p>PRESENT</p>\r\n<p>Do you see the bird?</p>\r\n<p>Yes, I see it.</p>\r\n<p>Does she see it?</p>\r\n<p>No, she does not see it.</p>\r\n<p>Do they see it?</p>\r\n<p>No, they don\'t see it.</p>\r\n<p>PAST</p>\r\n<p>Did you see the bird?</p>\r\n<p>Yes, I saw it.</p>\r\n<p>Did she see it?</p>\r\n<p>No, she did not see it.</p>\r\n<p>Did they see it?</p>\r\n<p>No, they didn\'t see it.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-08-04 01:19:06', '2019-08-04 01:36:56'),
(288, 2, 1, 6, 'Vocabulario Nuevo 5', 'lista-de-vocabulario-5', NULL, '<p>triste, deprimente, sombr&iacute;o, t&eacute;trico, tenebroso - l&uacute;gubre</p>\r\n<p>una persona que se jacta - fanfarr&oacute;n</p>\r\n<p>equipo - enseres</p>\r\n<p>mellow, que es dulce y amable - meloso</p>\r\n<p>que puede ser comprendido - concebible</p>\r\n<p>aware, consciente, al corriente, informado - al tanto de</p>\r\n<p>spoil, poner una cosa en mal estado o en peor estado del que ten&iacute;a - estropear</p>\r\n<p>de haber podido, nunca habria acabado asi</p>\r\n<p>me plantaria eligir a el - plantaria</p>\r\n<p>proponer, posar - plantear</p>\r\n<p>corregir o arreglar los errores o defectos, rectificar, reformar - enmendar</p>\r\n<p>cualidad o actitud de la persona que se mantiene en sus ideas, opiniones o deseos aun en contra de razones convincentes - turquedad</p>', 1, 42, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-08-04 01:30:49', '2019-08-06 05:36:36'),
(6, 1, 1, 3, 'Pronouns', 'subject-pronouns', NULL, '<p>The personal pronouns are: <strong>I, you</strong>,<strong> he</strong>,<strong> she</strong>,<strong> it</strong>, <strong>we</strong>, and <strong>they</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>I</strong> - is yourself.&nbsp;ex.&nbsp;<strong>I</strong> am cold.</p>\r\n<p><strong>You</strong> - is the person or persons you are talking to.&nbsp; It can also be used for more than one person (plural).&nbsp;ex. <strong>You</strong> are funny (singular).&nbsp; <strong>You </strong>are both funny (plural).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The other pronouns are used to replace a noun after it has been identified or mentioned.&nbsp; ex. The house is new.&nbsp; <strong>It</strong>&nbsp;is white.</p>\r\n<p><strong>He</strong> - is a male that you are talking about.&nbsp;ex.&nbsp;<strong>He </strong>is a father.</p>\r\n<p><strong>She </strong>- is a female that you are talking about.&nbsp;ex.&nbsp;<strong>She</strong> is a mother.</p>\r\n<p><strong>It</strong> - is a place or thing that you are talking about. ex. <strong>It</strong> is tall.</p>\r\n<p><strong>We</strong>&nbsp;- is yourself and one or more other people so it is plural.&nbsp; ex.&nbsp;<strong>We&nbsp;</strong>are happy.</p>\r\n<p><strong>They</strong> - is used for plural nouns.&nbsp; ex. The two houses are white.&nbsp; <strong>They</strong> are new.</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-note\">\r\n<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Unlike in some other languages, in English <strong>he</strong> and <strong>she</strong> are only used for people and sometimes for animals.&nbsp; For all other nouns, <strong>it </strong>is used.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Here are more examples of pronouns:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p><strong>We</strong> are fun.</p>\r\n<p><strong>They</strong> are Italian.</p>\r\n<p><strong>I</strong> am ready.</p>\r\n<p><strong>He</strong> is short.</p>\r\n<p><strong>It</strong> is hot.</p>\r\n<p><strong>She</strong> is thin.</p>\r\n</div>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 11:59:09', '2019-08-10 08:11:19'),
(7, 1, 1, 1, 'Introduction', 'introduction', 'Our simple approach to teaching English.', '<p>The best way to learn English is to build your vocabulary, learn the verbs tenses and the basic grammar rules, and then practice listening, speaking, and reading as much as possible.</p>\r\n<p>The goal of this course is to avoid long grammar explanations by showing the concepts in simple terms so that the student can focus on learning quickly and practice speaking and listening.</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-note\">\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> English is the most widely spoken language worldwide, with 1.5 billion speakers.&nbsp; It is the&nbsp;standard language for business, technology, and tourism.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Exercises</h3>\r\n<p>We teach English through friendly, interactive, and well-designed exercises. The exercises are full of the most commonly used English words so you can quickly build and practice your vocabulary at each step of the way.</p>\r\n<h3>Practice and Quizes</h3>\r\n<p>At the end of most sections, there is a quiz to test and reinforce what you have learned.&nbsp; The software also keeps track of your progress so you can return at anytime and continue where you left off.</p>\r\n<h3>Conversation</h3>\r\n<p>As an additional service, we have native English speakers who can help you with conversation and especially pronunciation.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 12:08:52', '2019-08-07 23:17:56'),
(8, 1, 1, 6, 'Describing with Adjectives', 'describing-with-adjectives', 'Describing People, Places, and Things', '<p>Adjectives are used to describe nouns.</p>\r\n<p>In English they are placed before the noun.</p>\r\n<p>For example:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>a <strong>tall</strong> tree</p>\r\n<p>the <strong>blue</strong> sky</p>\r\n<p>a <strong>big</strong> sheep</p>\r\n<p>a <strong>little</strong> girl</p>\r\n<p>a <strong>round</strong> planet</p>\r\n<p>a <strong>fast</strong> car</p>\r\n<p>the <strong>green</strong> grass</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When a sentence is using the verb <strong>To Be</strong> then an adjective can come after the verb.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For example:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>The tree is <strong>tall</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The sky is <strong>blue</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The sheep is <strong>big</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The girl is <strong>little</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The car is <strong>fast</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The grass is <strong>green</strong>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Summary</h3>\r\n<p>Adjectives are fun to use because they add colorful descriptions to the language.</p>\r\n<p>They usually go before the noun:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>The <strong>big</strong> house has a <strong>green</strong> door.</p>\r\n<p>The <strong>red </strong>car has <strong>silver</strong> wheels.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When using the verb <strong>To Be</strong>, the adjectives go after the verb:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>The house is <strong>big</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The car is <strong>red</strong>.</p>\r\n</div>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 12:43:44', '2019-07-17 06:38:51'),
(9, 2, 3, 2, 'Subjunctive Triggers No Pattern', 'subjunctive-triggers', NULL, '<p>a menos que - a menos que <strong>se indique</strong> lo contrario</p>\r\n<p>antes (de) que - antes de que me <strong>olvide</strong></p>\r\n<p>con tal (de) que - provided that</p>\r\n<p>cuando</p>\r\n<p>conviene que - it is advisable that</p>\r\n<p>despu&eacute;s (de) que</p>\r\n<p>dudar que&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>en caso de que</p>\r\n<p>en cuanto</p>\r\n<p>estar contento que</p>\r\n<p>hasta que</p>\r\n<p>insistir en que</p>\r\n<p>mandar que</p>\r\n<p>m&aacute;s vale que</p>\r\n<p>mientras que</p>\r\n<p>negar que</p>\r\n<p>ojal&aacute; que</p>\r\n<p>para que</p>\r\n<p>pedir que</p>\r\n<p>preferir que</p>\r\n<p>prohibir que</p>\r\n<p>puede ser que</p>\r\n<p>querer que</p>\r\n<p>recomendar que</p>\r\n<p>rogar que - to plead that</p>\r\n<p>sentir que - to regret that</p>\r\n<p>sin que&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>sugerir que</p>\r\n<p>tan pronto como</p>\r\n<p>temer que</p>\r\n<p>tener miedo de que</p>\r\n<p>a condici&oacute;n de que - a condici&oacute;n de que <strong>te vayas</strong> ahora</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 07:04:59', '2019-07-21 22:43:20'),
(23, 5, 1, 1, 'To Be: Present Tense', 'to-be--present-tense', NULL, '<p>The verb <strong>To Be</strong> describes the identity, qualities, or condition of a person, living thing, or object.</p>\r\n<p>Use the following to form the present tense of the verb <strong>To Be</strong>.</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-borderless\">\r\n<table class=\"table lesson-table-sm\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I am</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I am happy today.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You are smart.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He is my best friend.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She is busy.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It is true.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We are tired.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They are here.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-note\">\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> There are <em><strong>1.5 billion</strong></em> English speakers in the world.&nbsp; English is the standard language for international business, technology, and tourism.</p>\r\n</div>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-19 01:55:24', '2019-07-25 22:16:26'),
(22, 2, 3, 1, 'Subjunctive Triggers Simple', 'subjunctive-triggers-es-----que', 'Subjunctive triggers that use the pattern \'es word que\'', '<p>es aconsejable que - it&rsquo;s advisable that</p>\r\n<p>es bueno que</p>\r\n<p>es dif&iacute;cil que - it&rsquo;s unlikely that</p>\r\n<p>es dudoso que</p>\r\n<p>es f&aacute;cil que - it&rsquo;s likely that</p>\r\n<p>es fant&aacute;stico que</p>\r\n<p>es importante que</p>\r\n<p>es imposible que</p>\r\n<p>es improbable que</p>\r\n<p>es incierto que - it&rsquo;s uncertain that</p>\r\n<p>es incre&iacute;ble que</p>\r\n<p>es (una) l&aacute;stima que</p>\r\n<p>es malo que&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>es mejor que</p>\r\n<p>es menester que - it&rsquo;s necessary that</p>\r\n<p>es necesario que</p>\r\n<p>esperar que</p>\r\n<p>es posible que</p>\r\n<p>es preciso que - it&rsquo;s necessary that&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>es preferible que&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>es probable que</p>\r\n<p>es raro que</p>\r\n<p>es rid&iacute;culo que</p>\r\n<p>es terrible que&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-19 00:15:48', '2019-07-21 22:42:57'),
(21, 2, 3, 3, 'Subjunctive Triggers Negative', 'subjunctive-triggers-negative', NULL, '<p>no creer que</p>\r\n<p>no es cierto que</p>\r\n<p>no estar convencido de que</p>\r\n<p>no estar seguro de que</p>\r\n<p>no es verdad que</p>\r\n<p>no imaginarse que</p>\r\n<p>no parecer que&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>no pensar que</p>\r\n<p>no suponer que</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-19 00:12:42', '2019-07-21 22:43:36'),
(10, 3, 1, 1, 'Cosas Que Hacer', 'fix-lesson-index-on-tablet-size', 'Esta es la lista de cosas que hacer en el proyecto.', '<p><strong>PRIMERO</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contenido: English 1</li>\r\n<li>Agregar rastreador con stats, conteo de visitas, resultados de los ejercicios</li>\r\n<li>Agregar esquima de organizar lista de vocabulaio del usuario</li>\r\n<li>Agregar practica para las listas de vacuabulario de las lecciones</li>\r\n<li>Disenar esquima de traduccion</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>MISC</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Agregar buscada para cursos, lecciones, y vocab</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>LECCIONES</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cambiar las lecciones usar el estatus del lanzamiento release y wip</li>\r\n<li>Enchufla \'Mostrar Respuestas\' / review mode</li>\r\n<li>Si solo hay un capitulo, muestra secciones como curses en la primera pagina.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>OTRO</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Agrega boton flotante para volver a la parte superior de la pagina</li>\r\n<li>Agrestyles, global and course level. Overwrite lesson styles.</li>\r\n</ul>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-14 09:31:16', '2019-08-14 22:22:27'),
(306, 2, 5, 6, 'Ser en lugar de Estar', 'ser-en-lugar-de-estar', NULL, '<p>Use ser instead of estar for where an event takes place.</p>\r\n<p>La reuni&oacute;n es en mi oficina.</p>\r\n<p>La fiesta de cumplea&ntilde;os es en el restaurante.</p>\r\n<p>El evento es en el centro de la ciudad.</p>\r\n<p>La misa es en la catedral principal.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-08-09 06:16:00', '2019-08-09 07:03:09'),
(11, 2, 2, 2, 'Frases Avanzadas en Español 2', 'frases-avanzadas-en-espa--ol-2', 'El último vocabulario avanzado en español', '<p>Alta presi&oacute;n sangu&iacute;nea</p>\r\n<p>Reprender - La venta de un l&aacute;tigo para reprender a ni&ntilde;os causa controversia</p>\r\n<p>Reprender - Re&ntilde;ir a una persona o expresi&oacute;n de forma autoritaria y severa desaprobaci&oacute;n a causa de su actuaci&oacute;n o su comportamiento.</p>\r\n<p>Jalear - Animar o apoyar a una persona por lo que hace, especialmente con expresiones y gritos.</p>\r\n<p>en ambos sentidos - el tr&aacute;fico fue lento en ambos sentidos</p>\r\n<p>rendir&aacute;n cuentas - held accountable</p>\r\n<p>Chiringuito - Puesto de bebidas y comidas sencillas al aire libre, especialmente en la playa.</p>\r\n<p>Chinamo - Choza, barraca o cobertizo que se construye durante las fiestas populares para vender comidas y bebidas.</p>\r\n<p>Tajar - El se muestra tajante con los reporteros.</p>\r\n<p>u&ntilde;a y carne - Flesh and Bone</p>\r\n<p>esgrimir, esgrimiendo - wield, usar, ejercer, empunar, emplear, aprovechar</p>\r\n<p>empu&ntilde;ar -&nbsp;Tomar una cosa por la empu&ntilde;adura, especialmente un arma.&nbsp; \"empu&ntilde;ar una pistola; empu&ntilde;ar una espada; el retrato de Bonaparte en el puente de Areola le muestra &eacute;pico y juvenil, bajo el fuego enemigo, empu&ntilde;ando la bandera.\"</p>\r\n<p>tranquilizador - calmante, tranquilizador, dulce, analg&eacute;sico (soothing)</p>\r\n<p>Destreza - en la aplicaci&oacute;n de las destrezas de comprensi&oacute;n, lectura y escritura, as&iacute; como la novedad al interior</p>\r\n<p>Conforme avanza en el programa - As you advance</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-14 19:53:03', '2019-07-27 20:13:25'),
(12, 3, 2, 0, 'Lesson Topics', 'lesson-topics', NULL, '<p>Definite and Indefinite articles - the and a</p>\r\n<p>Determiners - what, which, whose</p>\r\n<p>Demonstrative Adjectives - this, that, these, those</p>\r\n<p>Personal Pronouns - i, you, he, she, it, we, they</p>\r\n<p>Possessive Adjectives - my, your, his, her, its, our, their</p>\r\n<p>Possessive Pronouns - mine, your, his, hers, its, theirs</p>\r\n<p>Quantifiers -A quantifier is a word or phrase which is used before a noun to indicate the amount or quantity:</p>\r\n<p>ordinal numbers, some, many, few, a, \'a lot of\', \'a few\'.</p>\r\n<p>Used as adjectives: one house, ordinal numbers, Many, few, a,</p>\r\n<p>Used as pronouns: one is enough. many go to work, few are old</p>\r\n<p>To Be: Present, Negative, Question</p>\r\n<p>To Be: Past Tense, Negative, Question</p>\r\n<p>To Have: Present, Negative, Question</p>\r\n<p>Simple Present Tense, Negative, Question</p>\r\n<p>Simple Past Tense, Negative, Question</p>\r\n<p>Simple Past Irregular Verbs 1 (don\'t use -ed)</p>\r\n<p>Simple Past Irregular Verbs 2 (don\'t use -ed)</p>\r\n<p>Simple Past Irregular Verbs 3 (don\'t use -ed)</p>\r\n<p>Prepositions in and on</p>\r\n<p>There is / There are, present, negative, question</p>\r\n<p>There is/are, past, negative, question&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Prepositions to, at</p>\r\n<p>Progressive Tense, present, negative, question</p>\r\n<p>Progressive Tense, past negative, question</p>\r\n<p>Prepositions: from and of</p>\r\n<p>Future Tense, future, negative, question</p>\r\n<p>Going to, future, negative, question</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-15 00:55:08', '2019-07-26 19:27:06'),
(29, 5, 2, 1, 'To Be: Present Tense: Negative Form', 'to-be--present-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>not</strong> after the verb <strong>To Be</strong> to create the negative form of the present tense.</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-borderless\">\r\n<div class=\"table-borderless\">\r\n<table class=\"table lesson-table-sm\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I am</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I am not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I am not ready.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>you are not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You are not ready.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>he is not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He is not my friend.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>she is not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She is not tall.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>it is not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It is not true.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>we are not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We are not tired.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>they are not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They are not pink.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>The negative form of the present tense of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.&nbsp; There is no contraction for <strong>am not</strong>.</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-borderless\">\r\n<table class=\"table lesson-table-sm\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I am not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I am not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I am not sick.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you are not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>you aren\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You aren\'t a teacher.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he is not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>he isn\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He isn\'t a lawyer.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she is not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>she isn\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She isn\'t ready.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it is not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>it isn\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It isn\'t a toy.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we are not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>we aren\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We aren\'t twins.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they are not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>they aren\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They aren\'t yellow.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-20 20:45:56', '2019-07-25 22:16:38'),
(30, 5, 2, 2, 'Vacabulary 1', 'vacabulary-1', 'Page 5', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the new vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>table</p>\r\n<p>city</p>\r\n<p>kid</p>\r\n<p>sister</p>\r\n<p>bus</p>\r\n<p>sister-in-law</p>\r\n<p>sour</p>\r\n<p>line</p>\r\n<p>neighbor</p>\r\n<p>cheese</p>\r\n<p>Italian</p>\r\n<p>early</p>\r\n<p>Spanish</p>\r\n<p>drawer</p>\r\n<p>empty</p>\r\n<p>pregnant</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-20 20:47:11', '2019-07-21 03:04:26'),
(31, 5, 2, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', 'Page 6', '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to express the negative form.&nbsp; Write the sentences once using <strong>am not</strong>, <strong>is not</strong> or <strong>are not</strong> and once using the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The cheese is on the table.</p>\r\n<p><input type=\"text\" /></p>\r\n<p><input type=\"text\" /></p>\r\n<p>She is my sister.</p>\r\n<p><input type=\"text\" /></p>\r\n<p><input type=\"text\" /></p>\r\n<p>My neighbors are Spanish.</p>\r\n<p><input type=\"text\" /></p>\r\n<p><input type=\"text\" /></p>\r\n<p>My sister-in-law is Italian.</p>\r\n<p><input type=\"text\" /></p>\r\n<p><input type=\"text\" /></p>\r\n<p>Diane is pregnant.</p>\r\n<p><input type=\"text\" /></p>\r\n<p><input type=\"text\" /></p>\r\n<p>The lines are sour.</p>\r\n<p>The bus is empty.</p>\r\n<p>The kids are early for class today.</p>\r\n<p>The drawers are empty.</p>\r\n<p>It is a nice city.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-20 20:51:18', '2019-07-20 21:03:32'),
(32, 5, 2, 4, 'Vocabulary 2', 'vocabulary-2', 'Page 7', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the new vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>boss</p>\r\n<p>mall</p>\r\n<p>far</p>\r\n<p>subway</p>\r\n<p>road</p>\r\n<p>eraser</p>\r\n<p>fair</p>\r\n<p>wide</p>\r\n<p>husband</p>\r\n<p>good</p>\r\n<p>idea</p>\r\n<p>store</p>\r\n<p>key</p>\r\n<p>office</p>\r\n<p>work</p>\r\n<p>book</p>\r\n<p>school</p>\r\n<p>ceiling</p>\r\n<p>wife</p>\r\n<p>boy</p>\r\n<p>dragonfly</p>\r\n<p>full</p>\r\n<p>white</p>\r\n<p>bowl</p>\r\n<p>black</p>\r\n<p>hand</p>\r\n<p>pen</p>\r\n<p>expensive</p>\r\n<p>late</p>\r\n<p>car</p>\r\n<p>garbage can</p>\r\n<p>garbage bag</p>\r\n<p>shelf</p>\r\n<p>pencil case</p>\r\n<p>shoe</p>\r\n<p>doctor</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-20 20:52:27', '2019-07-21 03:04:57'),
(33, 5, 2, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', 'Page 7, DONE', '<p>Use <strong>am not</strong> or the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong> to complete the following negative sentences.</p>\r\n<p>The subway <input type=\"text\" /> full.</p>\r\n<p>The windows <input type=\"text\" /> dirty.</p>\r\n<p>It <input type=\"text\" /> a dragonfly.</p>\r\n<p>The keys <input type=\"text\" /> in the car.</p>\r\n<p>The microwave oven <input type=\"text\" /> in the kitchen.</p>\r\n<p>My boss <input type=\"text\" /> at the office.</p>\r\n<p>The boys <input type=\"text\" /> in the tent.</p>\r\n<p>We <input type=\"text\" /> busy at work.</p>\r\n<p>My hands <input type=\"text\" /> dirty.</p>\r\n<p>The eraser <input type=\"text\" /> in the pencil case.</p>\r\n<p>She <input type=\"text\" /> a teacher in my school.</p>\r\n<p>The ceiling <input type=\"text\" /> white.</p>\r\n<p>The bowls <input type=\"text\" /> on the table.</p>\r\n<p>The garbage bags <input type=\"text\" /> in the drawar.</p>\r\n<p>The garbage can <input type=\"text\" /> full.</p>\r\n<p>The store <input type=\"text\" /> far.</p>\r\n<p>It <input type=\"text\" /> fair.</p>\r\n<p>The roads in the city <input type=\"text\" /> wide.</p>\r\n<p>My husband <input type=\"text\" /> a doctor.</p>\r\n<p>The pens <input type=\"text\" /> black.</p>\r\n<p>The books <input type=\"text\" /> on the shelf.</p>\r\n<p>The vacuum <input type=\"text\" /> in the basement.</p>\r\n<p>They <input type=\"text\" /> friends.</p>\r\n<p>The ribbon <input type=\"text\" /> red.</p>\r\n<p>She <input type=\"text\" /> late for class today.</p>\r\n<p>It <input type=\"text\" /> true.</p>\r\n<p>I <input type=\"text\" /> tired.</p>\r\n<p>Barry <input type=\"text\" /> a good student.</p>\r\n<p>The juice <input type=\"text\" /> cold.</p>\r\n<p>My wife <input type=\"text\" /> at the mall.</p>\r\n<p>The shoes <input type=\"text\" /> expensive.</p>\r\n<p>The students <input type=\"text\" /> tired today.</p>\r\n<p>The woman <input type=\"text\" /