(34, 5, 3, 1, 'To Be: Present Tense: Question Form', 'to-be--present-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place the verb <strong>To Be</strong> before the subject to create the question form of the present tense.</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-borderless\">\r\n<table class=\"table lesson-table-sm\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I am</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>am I</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Am I late?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>are you</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Are you my new boss?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>is he</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Is he your teacher?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>is she</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Is she your neighbor?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>is it</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Is it expensive?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>are we</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Are we early?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>are they</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Are they in the basement?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-20 22:34:59', '2019-07-25 22:17:11'),
(35, 5, 3, 2, 'Vocabulary 1', 'vocabulary-1', 'Page 9', '<p>wheel</p>\r\n<p>policeman</p>\r\n<p>goldfish</p>\r\n<p>sweet</p>\r\n<p>meeting</p>\r\n<p>serious</p>\r\n<p>English</p>\r\n<p>orange</p>\r\n<p>sharpener</p>\r\n<p>clothesline</p>\r\n<p>garage</p>\r\n<p>French</p>\r\n<p>brown</p>\r\n<p>downstairs</p>\r\n<p>pond</p>\r\n<p>bathroom</p>\r\n<p>outside</p>\r\n<p>toothbrush</p>\r\n<p>toothpaste</p>\r\n<p>bathing suit</p>\r\n<p>desk</p>\r\n<p>coat</p>\r\n<p>cow</p>\r\n<p>box</p>\r\n<p>calf</p>\r\n<p>frog</p>\r\n<p>poor</p>\r\n<p>very</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-20 22:43:33', '2019-07-20 22:44:55'),
(36, 5, 3, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', 'Page 10', '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions by placing the verb <strong>To Be</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>The wheels are in the garage.</p>\r\n<p>The sharpener is on my desk.</p>\r\n<p>The toothbrush and toothpaste are in the bathroom.</p>\r\n<p>My bathing suit is on the clothesline.</p>\r\n<p>I am in your English class.</p>\r\n<p>It is cold outside.</p>\r\n<p>He is a policeman in the city.</p>\r\n<p>The coats are on the floor.</p>\r\n<p>Joanne and Veronica are in a metting.</p>\r\n<p>The toys are in the box downstairs.</p>\r\n<p>The cow and calf are brown.</p>\r\n<p>The orange juice is sweet.</p>\r\n<p>The frogs are in the pond.</p>\r\n<p>The goldfish is in the bowl.</p>\r\n<p>You are serious.</p>\r\n<p>Marie is French.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-20 22:45:56', '2019-07-21 03:06:18'),
(37, 5, 3, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'exercise-2', 'Page 11', '<p>knife</p>\r\n<p>dishwasher</p>\r\n<p>fork</p>\r\n<p>bill</p>\r\n<p>correct</p>\r\n<p>living room</p>\r\n<p>clean</p>\r\n<p>real</p>\r\n<p>sharp</p>\r\n<p>lipstick</p>\r\n<p>oven</p>\r\n<p>bed</p>\r\n<p>funy</p>\r\n<p>pearl</p>\r\n<p>sheet</p>\r\n<p>turkey</p>\r\n<p>Chinese</p>\r\n<p>Mr.</p>\r\n<p>Scottish</p>\r\n<p>needle</p>\r\n<p>gate</p>\r\n<p>printer</p>\r\n<p>nail polish</p>\r\n<p>bird</p>\r\n<p>skunk</p>\r\n<p>pillow</p>\r\n<p>accountant</p>\r\n<p>ink</p>\r\n<p>fence</p>\r\n<p>thread</p>\r\n<p>curtain</p>\r\n<p>pen</p>\r\n<p>Mrs.</p>\r\n<p>pot</p>\r\n<p>birdhouse</p>\r\n<p>pan</p>\r\n<p>pig</p>\r\n<p>garden</p>\r\n<p>again</p>\r\n<p>there</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-20 22:50:18', '2019-07-20 22:52:10'),
(38, 5, 3, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', 'Page 11', '<p>Complete the following questions using the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>___ it cold in Canada?</p>\r\n<p>___ the skunks in the garden again.</p>\r\n<p>___ the needle and thread in the drawar?</p>\r\n<p>___ he a good accountant?</p>\r\n<p>___ they in the living room?</p>\r\n<p>___ the ink in the printer?</p>\r\n<p>___ the pots and pans clean?</p>\r\n<p>___ she your sister-in-law?</p>\r\n<p>___ the forks in the dishwasher?</p>\r\n<p>___ we ready?</p>\r\n<p>___ it a black pen?</p>\r\n<p>___ I nice?</p>\r\n<p>___ you busy today?</p>\r\n<p>___ the gate open?</p>\r\n<p>___ the fridge empty?</p>\r\n<p>___ Mr. and Mrs. Yee Chinese?</p>\r\n<p>___ the pillows on the bed?</p>\r\n<p>___ the fence white?</p>\r\n<p>___ the books on the shelf?</p>\r\n<p>___ the sheets on the clothesline?</p>\r\n<p>___ the curtains blue?</p>\r\n<p>___ the nail polish purple?</p>\r\n<p>___ the pearls real?</p>\r\n<p>___ Mrs. McDonald Scottish?</p>\r\n<p>___ the turkey in the oven?</p>\r\n<p>___ the birds in the birdhouse?</p>\r\n<p>___ the pigs in the pen?</p>\r\n<p>___ the knife sharp?</p>\r\n<p>___ the bill correct?</p>\r\n<p>___ the lipstick red or pink?</p>\r\n<p>___ they there?</p>\r\n<p>___ I funny?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-20 22:52:43', '2019-07-21 03:06:38'),
(39, 5, 4, 1, 'To Be: Past Tense', 'to-be--past-tense', NULL, '<p>The past tense of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> is created by using <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> in place of <strong>am</strong>, <strong>is</strong>, and <strong>are</strong>.</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-borderless\">\r\n<table class=\"table lesson-table-sm\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I am</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I was tired at school today.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>you were</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You were downstairs.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>he was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He was funny.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>she was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She was at work.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it is</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>it was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It was on the shelf.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>we were</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We were upstairs.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they are</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>they were</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They were here.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 02:37:54', '2019-07-25 22:17:16'),
(40, 5, 4, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', 'Page 13', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the new vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>snake</p>\r\n<p>diaper</p>\r\n<p>sorry</p>\r\n<p>beach</p>\r\n<p>pencil</p>\r\n<p>bag</p>\r\n<p>roommate</p>\r\n<p>laundry room</p>\r\n<p>bucket</p>\r\n<p>pocket</p>\r\n<p>farm</p>\r\n<p>minnow</p>\r\n<p>crust</p>\r\n<p>grandmother</p>\r\n<p>hairdresser</p>\r\n<p>exam</p>\r\n<p>thick</p>\r\n<p>pool</p>\r\n<p>washer</p>\r\n<p>dryer</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 02:43:11', '2019-07-21 02:44:49'),
(41, 5, 4, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', 'Page 14', '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the past tense by changing the present tense form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> to the past tense form.</p>\r\n<p>He is my roommate.</p>\r\n<p>It is in my pocket.</p>\r\n<p>The snake is in the garden.</p>\r\n<p>The diapers are in the bag.</p>\r\n<p>Lisa is sick.</p>\r\n<p>The kids are in the pool.</p>\r\n<p>The bucket is full of minnows.</p>\r\n<p>The washer and dryer are in the laundry room.</p>\r\n<p>I am in my office.</p>\r\n<p>The pencil is on the floor.</p>\r\n<p>Sorry that I am late.</p>\r\n<p>The flowers are for Jennifer.</p>\r\n<p>My grandmother is in the hospital.</p>\r\n<p>The exam is easy.</p>\r\n<p>The crust is very thick.</p>\r\n<p>The farm is very far.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 02:45:27', '2019-07-21 03:07:11'),
(42, 5, 4, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 15', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the new vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>huge</p>\r\n<p>ring</p>\r\n<p>crib</p>\r\n<p>story</p>\r\n<p>fresh</p>\r\n<p>soft</p>\r\n<p>spicy</p>\r\n<p>baby</p>\r\n<p>with</p>\r\n<p>wine</p>\r\n<p>cellar</p>\r\n<p>rake</p>\r\n<p>downtown</p>\r\n<p>broken</p>\r\n<p>godmother</p>\r\n<p>yesterday</p>\r\n<p>candle</p>\r\n<p>nurse</p>\r\n<p>cupboard</p>\r\n<p>asleep</p>\r\n<p>skating rink</p>\r\n<p>slipper</p>\r\n<p>wedding</p>\r\n<p>egg</p>\r\n<p>shower</p>\r\n<p>awake</p>\r\n<p>vase</p>\r\n<p>locker</p>\r\n<p>soup</p>\r\n<p>whale</p>\r\n<p>bedroom</p>\r\n<p>last night</p>\r\n<p>couch</p>\r\n<p>both</p>\r\n<p>library</p>\r\n<p>cafeteria</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 02:49:08', '2019-07-21 02:52:39'),
(55, 5, 6, 1, 'To Be: Past Tense: Question Form', 'to-be--past-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> before the subject to form questions in the past tense of the verb <strong>To Be</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>was I</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Was I funny?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you were</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>were you</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Were you awake?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>was he</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Was he very tall?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>was she</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Was she downtown?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>was it</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Was it on the floor?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we were</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>were we</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Were we fast?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they were</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>were they</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Were they asleep?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 22:15:51', '2019-07-25 22:17:27'),
(43, 5, 4, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', 'Page 15', '<p>Complete the following past tense sentences using <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The baby ___ in the crib.</p>\r\n<p>The candles ___ on the table.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ a good story.</p>\r\n<p>They ___ awake.</p>\r\n<p>My godmother ___ asleep on the couch.</p>\r\n<p>The wine ___ in the cellar.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ ready.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ in the shower.</p>\r\n<p>The bowls ___ in the cupboard.</p>\r\n<p>The girls ___ at the skating rink.</p>\r\n<p>The moon ___ bright last night.</p>\r\n<p>The juice ___ fresh.</p>\r\n<p>The eggs ___ on the counter.</p>\r\n<p>My sister ___ outside.</p>\r\n<p>The keys ___ in the car.</p>\r\n<p>The ring ___ expensive.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ at the wedding.</p>\r\n<p>The soup ___ hot and spicy.</p>\r\n<p>Both pillows ___ soft.</p>\r\n<p>Annie ___ a nurse.</p>\r\n<p>The flowers ___ in the vase.</p>\r\n<p>The rake ___ in the garage.</p>\r\n<p>My slippers ___ in the bedroom.</p>\r\n<p>The whale ___ huge.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ downtown yesterday.</p>\r\n<p>Chris ___ in the cafeteria with Robert.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ in my locker.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ at the library.</p>\r\n<p>The pool ___ small.</p>\r\n<p>The printer ___ broken.</p>\r\n<p>My pockets ___ full.</p>\r\n<p>The teachers ___ in the office.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 02:54:12', '2019-07-21 03:07:31'),
(102, 2, 1, 1, 'Vocabulario Nuevo 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>&nbsp;Hacer que disminuya la calidad o cantidad de algo. - Lastrar</p>\r\n<p>dimisi&oacute;n - renuncia</p>\r\n<p>P&iacute;caro/a, Picaresco/a - rogue, rogueish</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Quitar una cosa a una persona con violencia o con rapidez. - arrebatar</p>\r\n<p>en&eacute;simo - umpteenth</p>\r\n<p>servicio o pago que una persona o entidad hace a otra en correspondencia al que ha recibido o debe recibir - contraprestaci&oacute;n</p>\r\n<p>ser un hecho verdadero y exacto con seguridad para alguien - constar que</p>\r\n<p>electrodom&eacute;sticos - l&iacute;nea blanca</p>\r\n<p>pila o recipiente con llave de agua y desag&uuml;e en la cocina - fregadero</p>\r\n<p>pila o recipiente con llave de agua y desag&uuml;e en el ba&ntilde;o - lavabo</p>\r\n<p>pasar un l&iacute;quido de un recipiente a otro - verter</p>\r\n<p>verterse, hacer caer - derramar</p>\r\n<p>no llores sobre esto - la leche derramada</p>\r\n<p>dicho o hecho tonto o torpe - pendejada</p>\r\n<p>no estar de acuerdo - descrepar</p>\r\n<p>hacer un sonido monotono - zumbar</p>\r\n<p>militante (de la guerra) - b&eacute;lica</p>\r\n<p>pelear (expresar a una persona desaprobaci&oacute;n) - re&ntilde;ir</p>\r\n<p>luchar (___ con tantos problemas que casi se rinden) - lidiar</p>\r\n<p>antojo; whim - capricho</p>\r\n<p>algo sin raz&oacute;n (Nadie entiende los ___ del destino) - capricho</p>\r\n<p>fickle - caprichoso</p>\r\n<p>hablar entrecortado (repitiendo s&iacute;labas y sonidos) - tartamudear</p>\r\n<p>halting, faltering, vacilante - entrecortado</p>\r\n<p>&eacute;nfasis - hincapi&eacute;</p>\r\n<p>conferir un cargo - investidura</p>\r\n<p>alcanzable de comprar o conseguir, realizable - asequible</p>\r\n<p>enorme - ingente</p>\r\n<p>lazo, circuito, curva - bucle</p>\r\n<p>ponerse muy cerca - arrimarse</p>\r\n<p>evento; suceso; acto - acontecimiento</p>\r\n<p>suceder, producirse un hecho - acontecer</p>\r\n<p>bully, harass, atormentar, perseguir - acosar</p>\r\n<p>asegurarse de que se est&aacute; en lo cierto - cerciorarse</p>', 1, 42, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'font-size=\"150%\"', NULL, '2019-07-25 06:23:17', '2019-08-06 18:46:16'),
(44, 5, 5, 1, 'To Be: Past Tense: Negative Form', 'to-be--past-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>not</strong> after the past tense form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> to create a negative sentence.</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless lesson-table\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I was not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I was not sick yesterday.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you were</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>you were not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You were not at the beach.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>he was not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He was not at the meeting.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>she was not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She was not very nice.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it was</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>it was not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It was not on my desk.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we were</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>we were not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We were not late.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they were</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>they were not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They were not ready.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>The negative form of the past tense of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>wasn\'t</strong> or <strong>weren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless lesson-table\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I was not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I wasn\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I wasn\'t tired last night.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you were not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>you weren\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You weren\'t at work today.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he was not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>he wasn\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He wasn\'t serious.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she was not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>she wasn\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She wasn\'t here yesterday.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we were not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>we weren\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We weren\'t at the libarary.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they were not</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>they weren\'t</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They weren\'t busy last night.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 04:21:07', '2019-07-25 22:17:21'),
(45, 5, 5, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', 'Page 17', '<p>dress</p>\r\n<p>purple</p>\r\n<p>tree</p>\r\n<p>raccoon</p>\r\n<p>waitress</p>\r\n<p>fast</p>\r\n<p>list</p>\r\n<p>year</p>\r\n<p>joke</p>\r\n<p>plate</p>\r\n<p>play (noun)</p>\r\n<p>name</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 04:32:27', '2019-07-21 04:33:08'),
(46, 5, 5, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', 'Page 18', '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to express the negative form.&nbsp; Write the sentence once using <strong>was not</strong> or <strong>were not</strong> and once using the contractions <strong>wasn\'t</strong> or <strong>weren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The dress was blue.</p>\r\n<p>The couch in the living room was dirty.</p>\r\n<p>They were very fast.</p>\r\n<p>It was a good joke.</p>\r\n<p>The raccoons were in the tree.</p>\r\n<p>The slippers were purple.</p>\r\n<p>We were at the play last night.</p>\r\n<p>The plates were in the dishwasher.</p>\r\n<p>Karen was a waitress for three years.</p>\r\n<p>My name was on the list.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 04:33:26', '2019-07-21 04:35:59'),
(47, 5, 5, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 19', '<p>phone</p>\r\n<p>quiet</p>\r\n<p>mark</p>\r\n<p>clever</p>\r\n<p>landlord</p>\r\n<p>butter</p>\r\n<p>deep</p>\r\n<p>loud</p>\r\n<p>jam</p>\r\n<p>off</p>\r\n<p>binder</p>\r\n<p>shaver</p>\r\n<p>nest</p>\r\n<p>right answer</p>\r\n<p>powder</p>\r\n<p>stain</p>\r\n<p>funeral</p>\r\n<p>Greek</p>\r\n<p>polite</p>\r\n<p>vegetable</p>\r\n<p>stove</p>\r\n<p>cat</p>\r\n<p>ugly</p>\r\n<p>slide</p>\r\n<p>horn</p>\r\n<p>sock</p>\r\n<p>long</p>\r\n<p>big</p>\r\n<p>lake</p>\r\n<p>toolbox</p>\r\n<p>ground</p>\r\n<p>stroller</p>\r\n<p>rat</p>\r\n<p>movie</p>\r\n<p>snowstorm</p>\r\n<p>light</p>\r\n<p>hammer</p>\r\n<p>bread</p>\r\n<p>museum</p>\r\n<p>on</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 04:36:24', '2019-07-21 04:37:57'),
(48, 5, 5, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', 'Page 19', '<p>Use the contractions <strong>wasn\'t</strong> or <strong>weren\'t</strong> to complete the following negative sentences.</p>\r\n<p>My marks ___ good at school last year.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ a raccoon; it was a skunk.</p>\r\n<p>The stain on the floor ___ big.</p>\r\n<p>The vegetables ___ fresh.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ very polite with the landlord.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ the right answer.</p>\r\n<p>The horn in my car ___ loud.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ at the funeral.</p>\r\n<p>The kids ___ quiet today in class.</p>\r\n<p>The grass ___ long.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ very clever.</p>\r\n<p>The lake ___ deep.</p>\r\n<p>The baby ___ in the stroller.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ on the table.</p>\r\n<p>My socks ___ on the clothesline.</p>\r\n<p>The shaver ___ in the bathroom.</p>\r\n<p>The bread and butter ___ on the counter.</p>\r\n<p>The museum ___ very big.</p>\r\n<p>The rats ___ in the cellar.</p>\r\n<p>The nest ___ on the ground.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ on the phone.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ a big snowstorm.</p>\r\n<p>The binders ___ in my locker.</p>\r\n<p>The man ___ Greek; he was Italian.</p>\r\n<p>The jam ___ in the fridge.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ a good movie.</p>\r\n<p>The lights ___ on.</p>\r\n<p>The stove ___ off.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ ugly.</p>\r\n<p>The cat ___ black.</p>\r\n<p>The hammer ___ in the toolbox.</p>\r\n<p>The powder ___ on the shelf.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-21 04:38:10', '2019-07-21 04:43:34'),
