(235, 5, 40, 1, 'Be Going To: Future Tense', 'be-going-to--future-tense', NULL, '<p>The future tense can also be expressed by using <strong>be going to</strong>.&nbsp; Use the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> for each person.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb always follows <strong>be going to</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am going to explain</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am going to explain it to you again.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you are going to need</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You are going to need a hammer.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he is going to answer</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He is going to answer the question.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she is going to have</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She is going to have a baby.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it going to be</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It is going to be expensive.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we are going to prove</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We are going to prove it to you.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they are going to meet</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They are going to meet downtown.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:16:52', '2019-07-27 20:20:48'),
(86, 5, 11, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', 'Page 41', '<p>scarf</p>\r\n<p>dove</p>\r\n<p>lease</p>\r\n<p>rights</p>\r\n<p>tight</p>\r\n<p>until</p>\r\n<p>flip-flops</p>\r\n<p>important</p>\r\n<p>everything</p>\r\n<p>appointment</p>\r\n<p>project</p>\r\n<p>meat loaf</p>\r\n<p>pager</p>\r\n<p>same</p>\r\n<p>deadline</p>\r\n<p>wing</p>\r\n<p>celebration</p>\r\n<p>Thanksgiving</p>\r\n<p>Christmas Eve</p>\r\n<p>phone number</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 23:27:04', '2019-07-22 23:27:51'),
(28, 2, 1, 4, 'Palabras Nuevas 1', 'palabras-nuevas-1', 'Solo palabras.', '<p>b&eacute;lica - militante (belicoso, de la guerra o lo relacionado con la lucha armada.)</p>\r\n<p>re&ntilde;ir - pelear (Expresar a una persona desaprobaci&oacute;n sobre su actuaci&oacute;n o su comportamiento, mediante el tono, palabras y gestos de enojo.)</p>\r\n<p>lidiar - luchar (Lidiaron ferozmente con el ej&eacute;rcito enemigo y resultaron victoriosos. Lidiaron con tantos problemas que casi se rinden.&nbsp; Hay que lidiar con clientes caprichosos todos los d&iacute;as. )</p>\r\n<p>capricho - antojo (Tengo un capricho de chocolate.)&nbsp; algo sin raz&oacute;n (Nadie entiende los caprichos del destino.)</p>\r\n<p>caprichoso - fickle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>tartamudear - hablar entrecortado (Hablar con pronunciaci&oacute;n entrecortada y repitiendo algunas s&iacute;labas y sonidos.)</p>\r\n<p>entrecortado - vacilante (Que se emite con interrupciones muy breves y continuadas.&nbsp; Halting, faltering, vacilante.)</p>\r\n<p>hincapi&eacute; - &eacute;nfasis (el presidente hizo hincapi&eacute; en la necesidad de modificar la pol&iacute;tica econ&oacute;mica.)</p>\r\n<p>investidura - conferir un cargo (El acto y la consecuencia de investir. Refiere a conferir un cargo o una dignidad de importancia.)</p>\r\n<p>asequible - alcanzable (Que puede alcanzarse, conseguirse, comprarse o pagarse.)</p>\r\n<p>gesti&oacute;n p&uacute;blica - Promover el desarrollo econ&oacute;mico y social</p>\r\n<p>ingente - enorme (Las grandes empresas necesitan una ingente cantidad de datos para tomar decisiones importantes.)</p>\r\n<p>bucle - lazo (Conjunto de instrucciones cuya ejecuci&oacute;n se repite hasta que una determinada condici&oacute;n de salida se vea satisfecha. bucle infinito, circuito, curva, presilla, gaza)</p>\r\n<p>arrimarse - acercarse (ponerse muy cerca, juntarse, afiliarse)</p>\r\n<p>malabarear - hacer juegos malabares</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-19 22:20:25', '2019-07-27 20:00:51'),
(85, 5, 11, 1, 'To Have: Present Tense: Question Form', 'to-have--present-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>do</strong> or <strong>does</strong> before the subject to create questions with the verb <strong>To Have</strong>.&nbsp; As with the negative form, <strong>have</strong> is used for all persons and never <strong>has</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>do I have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Do I have good skills for the job?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>do you have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Do you have a headache?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he has</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>does he have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Does he have a good report card?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she has</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>does she have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Does she have a red binder?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it has</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>does it have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Does it have a long tail?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>do we have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Do we have a meeting?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>do they have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Do they have relatives in Montreal?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 23:23:04', '2019-07-25 22:18:56'),
