(91, 10, 1, 6, 'North America', 'north-america', 'Capital cities of the 30 countries of North America and the Caribbean.', '<p>Canada - Ottawa</p>\r\n<p>USA - Washington D.C.</p>\r\n<p>Mexico - Mexico City</p>\r\n<p>Guatemala - Guatemala City</p>\r\n<p>El Salvador - San Salvador</p>\r\n<p>Hondurus - Tegucigalpa</p>\r\n<p>Belize - Belmopan</p>\r\n<p>Nicaragua - Managua</p>\r\n<p>Costa Rica - San Jose</p>\r\n<p>Panama - Panama City</p>', 1, 42, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'prompt=\"What is the capital of:\"; prompt-reverse=\"What country is this the capital of:\"; question-count=\"20\"; font-size=\"200%\";', NULL, '2019-07-23 04:24:54', '2019-08-07 22:05:37'),
(92, 5, 12, 1, 'The Simple Present Tense', 'the-simple-present-tense', NULL, '<p>The simple present tense is used when stating general facts or true statements that have no time.&nbsp; Add <strong>-s</strong> to the verb for <strong>he</strong>, <strong>she</strong>, and <strong>it</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I need</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I need a new computer.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you need</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You need a good lawyer.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he needs</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He needs a roommate.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she needs</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She needs a blanket.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it needs</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It needs a lot of work.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we need</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We need a flashlight.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they need</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They need a new fridge.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Add <strong>-es</strong> to verbs when using <strong>he</strong>, <strong>she</strong>, and <strong>it</strong> if the verb:</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>ends with z, s, x, ss, ch, or sh</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>ends with o</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>ends with y preceded by a consonant -- change the y to i before adding -es</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I wash the car.</td>\r\n<td>I go to school.</td>\r\n<td>I try very hard.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>You wash the car.</td>\r\n<td>You go to school.</td>\r\n<td>You try very hard.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>He washes the car.</td>\r\n<td>He goes to school.</td>\r\n<td>He tries very hard.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>She washes the car.</td>\r\n<td>She goes to school.</td>\r\n<td>She tries very hard.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>It washes the car.</td>\r\n<td>It goes to school.</td>\r\n<td>It tries very hard.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>We wash the car.</td>\r\n<td>We go to school.</td>\r\n<td>We try very hard.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>They wash the car.</td>\r\n<td>They go to school.</td>\r\n<td>They try very hard.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-23 09:43:21', '2019-07-25 22:19:10'),
(93, 5, 12, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', 'Page 45', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to amaze</p>\r\n<p>to cry</p>\r\n<p>to guard</p>\r\n<p>to jump</p>\r\n<p>to blush</p>\r\n<p>to smoke</p>\r\n<p>to help</p>\r\n<p>to see</p>\r\n<p>to kiss</p>\r\n<p>to go</p>\r\n<p>to flush</p>\r\n<p>to scratch</p>\r\n<p>village</p>\r\n<p>toilet</p>\r\n<p>knight</p>\r\n<p>cigarette</p>\r\n<p>king</p>\r\n<p>every</p>\r\n<p>American</p>\r\n<p>kingdom</p>\r\n<p>castle</p>\r\n<p>apple</p>\r\n<p>caramel</p>\r\n<p>people</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-23 09:53:03', '2019-07-23 09:55:01'),
(94, 5, 12, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', 'Page 46', '<p>He (to smoke) American cigarettes.</p>\r\n<p>Karen (to blush) when she (to see) that boy.</p>\r\n<p>I (to love) caramel apple cake.</p>\r\n<p>He (to cry) like a baby.</p>\r\n<p>It (to amaze) me.</p>\r\n<p>It (to jump) very high.</p>\r\n<p>He (to kiss) all the girls in school.</p>\r\n<p>My cats (to scratch) the furniture.</p>\r\n<p>They (to help) many people in the village.</p>\r\n<p>The knights (to guard) the king and castle in the kingdom.</p>\r\n<p>He never (to flush) the toilet.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-23 09:55:19', '2019-07-23 09:57:35'),
(95, 5, 12, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 47', '<p>to crush</p>\r\n<p>to spoil</p>\r\n<p>to explain</p>\r\n<p>to manage</p>\r\n<p>to dream</p>\r\n<p>to own</p>\r\n<p>to do</p>\r\n<p>to follow</p>\r\n<p>to whisper</p>\r\n<p>to carry</p>\r\n<p>to make&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>to push</p>\r\n<p>to drive</p>\r\n<p>to melt</p>\r\n<p>to buy</p>\r\n<p>to eat</p>\r\n<p>to fear</p>\r\n<p>to owe</p>\r\n<p>to earn</p>\r\n<p>to obey</p>\r\n<p>paramedic</p>\r\n<p>lemon</p>\r\n<p>money</p>\r\n<p>stretcher</p>\r\n<p>carriage</p>\r\n<p>perfume</p>\r\n<p>raw</p>\r\n<p>bank</p>\r\n<p>spring</p>\r\n<p>local</p>\r\n<p>everywhere</p>\r\n<p>laundromat</p>\r\n<p>patient</p>\r\n<p>rule</p>\r\n<p>cottage</p>\r\n<p>tea</p>\r\n<p>laundry</p>\r\n<p>child</p>\r\n<p>onion</p>\r\n<p>grape</p>\r\n<p>housework</p>\r\n<p>restaurant</p>\r\n<p>waterfall</p>\r\n<p>nothing</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-23 09:58:00', '2019-07-23 10:00:18'),
(96, 5, 12, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', 'Page 47', '<p>Complete the following sentences with the correct form of the simple present tense using the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>My teacher ___ [to explain] everything.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ [to whisper] in class.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ [to crush] grapes to make wine.</p>\r\n<p>Lisa ___ [to buy] a lot of perfume.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ [to do] the housework for my mother.</p>\r\n<p>They ___ [to earn] a lot of money.</p>\r\n<p>Linda ___ [to work] downtown.</p>\r\n<p>My uncle ___ [to manage] a restaurant.</p>\r\n<p>The paramedics ___ [to carry] the patient on a stretcher.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ [to owe] me money.</p>\r\n<p>My grandmother ___ [to eat] raw onions.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ [to fear] nothing.</p>\r\n<p>They ___ [to follow] me everywhere.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ [to work] in the local bank.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ [to drink] tea with lemon.</p>\r\n<p>Jessica ___ [to push] the baby in a carriage.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ [to spoil] his child.</p>\r\n<p>Connie ___ [to dream] about waterfalls.</p>\r\n<p>Leo ___ [to drive] to work.</p>\r\n<p>My husband ___ [to do] the laundry.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ [to go] to the laundromat every week.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ [to own] a cottage in the country.</p>\r\n<p>The boys ___ [to obey] the rules in class.</p>\r\n<p>The snow ___ [to melt] in the spring.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-24 07:52:56', '2019-07-25 04:27:08'),
(97, 5, 13, 1, 'The Simple Present Tense: Negative Form', 'the-simple-present-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>do not</strong> or <strong>does not</strong> before the verb to create the negative form of the simple present tense.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb is always used.&nbsp; Never add <strong>-s</strong> to <strong>he</strong>, <strong>she</strong>, and <strong>it</strong> in the negative form of the simple present tense.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I do not wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I do not wear orange.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>you do not wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You do not wear perfume.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he wears</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>he does not wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He does not wear diapers.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she wears</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>she does not wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She does not wear a watch.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it wears</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>it does not wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It does not wear shoes.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>we do not wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We do not wear slippers.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>they do not wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They do not wear nail polish.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the simple present tense can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>don\'t</strong> or <strong>doesn\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I do not drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I don\'t drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I don\'t drink apple juice.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you do not drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>you don\'t drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You don\'t drink wine.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he does not drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>he doesn\'t drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He doesn\'t drink lemon juice.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she does not drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>she doesn\'t drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She doesn\'t drink milk.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it does not drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>it doesn\'t drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It doesn\'t drink water.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we do not drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>we don\'t drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We don\'t drink or smoke.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they do not drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>they don\'t drink</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They don\'t drink and drive.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-24 07:59:46', '2019-07-25 22:19:18'),
(98, 5, 13, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', 'Page 49', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to sell</p>\r\n<p>to yell</p>\r\n<p>to collect</p>\r\n<p>to snore</p>\r\n<p>to trust</p>\r\n<p>to dislike</p>\r\n<p>to believe</p>\r\n<p>to swear</p>\r\n<p>meat</p>\r\n<p>giant</p>\r\n<p>language</p>\r\n<p>coin</p>\r\n<p>fish</p>\r\n<p>several</p>\r\n<p>sewing machine</p>\r\n<p>foreign</p>', 1, 20, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-24 08:07:59', '2019-08-11 22:56:34'),
(99, 5, 13, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', 'Page 50', '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to express the negative form of the simple present tense.&nbsp; Write the sentence one using <strong>do not</strong> or <strong>does not</strong> and once using the contractions <strong>don\'t</strong> or <strong>doesn\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>My husband snores every night.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>I believe your story about the giant monkeys.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>Nancy and Yvan collect coins.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>She speaks several foreign languages.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>It dislikes fish.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>Ron swears and yells in class.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>Sara sells sewing machine.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>I trust you.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>We eat meat.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-24 08:09:52', '2019-07-24 08:13:03'),
(100, 5, 13, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 51', '<p>to bother</p>\r\n<p>to gossip</p>\r\n<p>to live</p>\r\n<p>to smell</p>\r\n<p>to learn</p>\r\n<p>to know</p>\r\n<p>to hurt</p>\r\n<p>to iron</p>\r\n<p>to deserve</p>\r\n<p>to sneeze</p>\r\n<p>to study</p>\r\n<p>to travel</p>\r\n<p>to listen</p>\r\n<p>to cook</p>\r\n<p>to cough</p>\r\n<p>to laugh</p>\r\n<p>to belong</p>\r\n<p>to forgive</p>\r\n<p>to feed</p>\r\n<p>to write</p>\r\n<p>stray</p>\r\n<p>coffee</p>\r\n<p>hard</p>\r\n<p>towel</p>\r\n<p>well</p>\r\n<p>pancake</p>\r\n<p>office</p>\r\n<p>ponytail</p>\r\n<p>clothes</p>\r\n<p>alone</p>\r\n<p>cotton candy</p>\r\n<p>cockroach</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-24 08:13:24', '2019-07-24 08:15:03'),
(101, 5, 13, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', 'Page 51', '<p>Complete the following sentences using the contractions <strong>don\'t</strong> or <strong>doesn\'t</strong> to create the negative form of the simple present tense.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ work well.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ feed the stray cats.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ dream a lot.</p>\r\n<p>Mark ___ want pancakes for breakfast.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ iron my clothes.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ bother me.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ write to Bob.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ cook every night.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ listen to me.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ travel alone.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ know you.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ hurt.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ deserve that.</p>\r\n<p>They ___ like cockroaches.</p>\r\n<p>Roger ___ want cotton candy.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ owe you money.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ sneeze all the time.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ drink coffee.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ smell good.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ cough at night.</p>\r\n<p>My dog ___ snore.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ laugh a lot.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ study very hard.</p>\r\n<p>Betty ___ gossip in the office.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ forgive you.</p>\r\n<p>They ___ learn a lot in class.</p>\r\n<p>Glenn ___ live here.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ belong to you.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ need a towel.</p>\r\n<p>Latonya ___ want a ponytail in her hair.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-24 08:15:35', '2019-07-25 09:47:47'),
(103, 5, 14, 1, 'Simple Present Tense: Question Form', 'simple-present-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place do or does before the subject to create questions in the simple present tense.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb is used when creating questions in the simple present tense.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I dream</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>do I dream</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Do I dream a lot?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you work</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>do you work</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Do you work well?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he sees</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>does he see</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Does he see the clock?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she wears</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>does she wear</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Does she wear flip-flops?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it hates</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>does it hate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Does it hate milk?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we want</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>do we want</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Do we want a dog?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they own</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>do they own</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Do they own the house?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 09:48:23', '2019-07-25 22:19:25'),
(104, 5, 14, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', 'Page 53', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to touch</p>\r\n<p>to scream</p>\r\n<p>to skate</p>\r\n<p>to cost</p>\r\n<p>to read</p>\r\n<p>to boil</p>\r\n<p>to put</p>\r\n<p>to play</p>\r\n<p>mortgage</p>\r\n<p>on time</p>\r\n<p>afternoon</p>\r\n<p>pepper</p>\r\n<p>newspaper</p>\r\n<p>everything</p>\r\n<p>night</p>\r\n<p>salt</p>\r\n<p>train</p>\r\n<p>soldier</p>\r\n<p>dough</p>\r\n<p>crown</p>\r\n<p>hobby</p>\r\n<p>fox</p>\r\n<p>horror</p>\r\n<p>woods</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 09:52:45', '2019-07-25 09:53:52'),
(105, 5, 14, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', 'Page 54', '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the question form of the simple present tense.&nbsp; Place <strong>do</strong> and <strong>does</strong> before the subject and use the single form of the verb.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>She skates in the morning.</p>\r\n<p>They boil the vegetables</p>\r\n<p>He sleeps in the afternoon.</p>\r\n<p>The boys play chess at night.</p>\r\n<p>You pay the mortgage on time.</p>\r\n<p>She reads the English newspaper.</p>\r\n<p>They drive to work together.</p>\r\n<p>It costs $20 to travel by train to the city.</p>\r\n<p>She screams when she watches horror movies.</p>\r\n<p>She wants a new hobby.</p>\r\n<p>The king wears a red velvet crown.</p>\r\n<p>Bobby plays with toy soldiers.</p>\r\n<p>You put salt and pepper in the dough.</p>\r\n<p>Jackie touches everything in my office.</p>\r\n<p>You see the fox in the woods.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 09:54:06', '2019-07-25 09:57:54'),
(106, 5, 14, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 55', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to agree</p>\r\n<p>to annoy</p>\r\n<p>to increase</p>\r\n<p>to disturb</p>\r\n<p>to interest</p>\r\n<p>to participate</p>\r\n<p>to chase</p>\r\n<p>to weigh</p>\r\n<p>to rent</p>\r\n<p>to fish</p>\r\n<p>to feed</p>\r\n<p>to walk</p>\r\n<p>to mix</p>\r\n<p>to dye</p>\r\n<p>to snow</p>\r\n<p>to park</p>\r\n<p>credit card</p>\r\n<p>piggy bank</p>\r\n<p>cigar</p>\r\n<p>lobster</p>\r\n<p>house</p>\r\n<p>noise</p>\r\n<p>minimum wage</p>\r\n<p>smoke</p>\r\n<p>truth</p>\r\n<p>pea</p>\r\n<p>children</p>\r\n<p>facecloth</p>\r\n<p>change</p>\r\n<p>worm</p>\r\n<p>coupon</p>\r\n<p>sick</p>\r\n<p>driveway</p>\r\n<p>pound</p>\r\n<p>glove</p>\r\n<p>mushroom</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 09:58:14', '2019-07-25 10:00:06'),
(107, 5, 14, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', 'Page 55', '<p>Complete the following sentences using <strong>do</strong> or <strong>does</strong> to create questions in the simple present tense.</p>\r\n<p>___ he annoy you?</p>\r\n<p>___ you pay with your credit card?</p>\r\n<p>___ it snow in your country?</p>\r\n<p>___ you need change?</p>\r\n<p>___ we agree?</p>\r\n<p>___ the minimum wage increase every year?</p>\r\n<p>___ you need a facecloth?</p>\r\n<p>___ he know the truth?</p>\r\n<p>___ you see the smoke?</p>\r\n<p>___ Chris and Jim rest a house?</p>\r\n<p>___ Joan have black gloves?</p>\r\n<p>___ you feel sick?</p>\r\n<p>___ he park in the driveway?</p>\r\n<p>___ it interest you?</p>\r\n<p>___ they want the coupons?</p>\r\n<p>___ she mix the eggs with the milk?</p>\r\n<p>___ the noise disturb you?</p>\r\n<p>___ the children like peas?</p>\r\n<p>___ they walk to school?</p>\r\n<p>___ your dog chase cats?</p>\r\n<p>___ it weigh twenty pounds?</p>\r\n<p>___ you eat lobster?</p>\r\n<p>___ she have a piggy bank?</p>\r\n<p>___ you fish with worms?</p>\r\n<p>___ Jerry smoke cigars?</p>\r\n<p>___ you dye your hair?</p>\r\n<p>___ they like mushrooms?</p>\r\n<p>___ Leslie participate at school?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 10:00:19', '2019-07-25 10:04:19'),
(108, 5, 15, 1, 'Possessive Adjectives', 'possessive-adjectives', NULL, '<p>Possessive adjectives are used to show ownership or possession of someone or something.&nbsp; They are placed before the noun.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>my</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I drink my coffee.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>your</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You drive your car.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>his</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He needs his screwdriver.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>her</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She wears her slippers.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>its</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It chases its tail.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>our</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We want our money.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>their</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They help their kids.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 10:04:52', '2019-07-25 22:19:34'),
(109, 5, 15, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', 'Page 57', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to dress</p>\r\n<p>to open</p>\r\n<p>to keep</p>\r\n<p>to lick</p>\r\n<p>to take</p>\r\n<p>to wash</p>\r\n<p>to burn</p>\r\n<p>to visit</p>\r\n<p>to bite</p>\r\n<p>to wipe</p>\r\n<p>to hide</p>\r\n<p>to forget</p>\r\n<p>master</p>\r\n<p>sponge</p>\r\n<p>under</p>\r\n<p>homework</p>\r\n<p>submarine</p>\r\n<p>mail</p>\r\n<p>sleeve</p>\r\n<p>sailor</p>\r\n<p>jewel</p>\r\n<p>apartment</p>\r\n<p>stair</p>\r\n<p>carpet</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 10:07:43', '2019-07-25 10:09:03'),
(110, 5, 15, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', 'Page 58', '<p>Rewrite the following sentences by choosing the correct possessive adjective indicated in parenthesis that refers back to the subject pronoun.</p>\r\n<p>She visits [our, their, her] relatives every summer. - her</p>\r\n<p>We hide [their, our, your] money under the carpet in the master bedroom. - our</p>\r\n<p>They keep [her, his, their] jewels in a jewelry box. - their</p>\r\n<p>I wash [your, my, his] stairs with a sponge. - my</p>\r\n<p>He passes all [our, her, his] exams. - his</p>\r\n<p>She dresses [our, her, its] dolls in pink. - her</p>\r\n<p>I open [your, our, my] mail after breakfast. - my</p>\r\n<p>He bites [my, our, his] nails. - his</p>\r\n<p>We rent [my, our, its] aparment. - our</p>\r\n<p>It licks [its, his, their] paws. - its</p>\r\n<p>I burn [your, my, our] marshmellows. - my</p>\r\n<p>Jeff takes [his, our, her] pills in the morning. - his</p>\r\n<p>The boys forget [my, our, their] homework every day. - their</p>\r\n<p>It bites [its, her, his] tail. - its</p>\r\n<p>She dyes [her, your, our] hair. - her</p>', 1, 4, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:14:52', '2019-07-25 21:28:41'),
(111, 5, 15, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 59', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to ride</p>\r\n<p>to fry</p>\r\n<p>to sail</p>\r\n<p>to sell</p>\r\n<p>to fly</p>\r\n<p>to greet</p>\r\n<p>to give</p>\r\n<p>to protect</p>\r\n<p>to curl</p>\r\n<p>to leave</p>\r\n<p>to argue</p>\r\n<p>to cut</p>\r\n<p>to hang</p>\r\n<p>to lace</p>\r\n<p>to use</p>\r\n<p>to demand</p>\r\n<p>world</p>\r\n<p>boat</p>\r\n<p>sand</p>\r\n<p>market</p>\r\n<p>around</p>\r\n<p>water</p>\r\n<p>bike</p>\r\n<p>field</p>\r\n<p>head</p>\r\n<p>skate</p>\r\n<p>lawn mower</p>\r\n<p>freedom</p>\r\n<p>day care</p>\r\n<p>footprint</p>\r\n<p>fireman</p>\r\n<p>kite</p>\r\n<p>week</p>\r\n<p>skim</p>\r\n<p>diary</p>\r\n<p>boot</p>\r\n<p>curling iron</p>\r\n<p>sunglasses</p>\r\n<p>arena</p>\r\n<p>fireplace</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:29:47', '2019-07-25 21:31:30'),
(112, 5, 15, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', 'Page 59', '<p>Complete the sentences using the correct possessive adjective according to the subject.</p>\r\n<p>They sail ___ boat around the world. - their</p>\r\n<p>She fries ___ eggs in butter. - her</p>\r\n<p>We give ___ old cothes to Peter. - our</p>\r\n<p>I ride ___ bike to school. - my</p>\r\n<p>She curls ___ hair with a curling iron. - her</p>\r\n<p>You need ___ dark sunglasses. - your</p>\r\n<p>I lace ___ skates at the arena. - my</p>\r\n<p>It drinks ___ water. - its</p>\r\n<p>We sell ___ vegetables at the market. - our</p>\r\n<p>The fireman wears ___ black boots - his</p>\r\n<p>The twins love and protect ___ brother. - their</p>\r\n<p>I greet ___ guests. - my</p>\r\n<p>They argue with ___ neighbors. - their</p>\r\n<p>He needs ___ lawyer. - his</p>\r\n<p>We demand ___ rights. - our</p>\r\n<p>He uses ___ lawn mower to cut the grass. - his</p>\r\n<p>I scratch ___ head. - my</p>\r\n<p>She hangs ___ clothes on the clothesline. - her</p>\r\n<p>They clean ___ fireplace every week. - their</p>\r\n<p>I drink ___ tea with skim milk. - my</p>\r\n<p>Laura loves ___ husband. - her</p>\r\n<p>You want ___ freedom. - your</p>\r\n<p>We leave ___ kids at the daycare. - our</p>\r\n<p>She writes in ___ diary. - her</p>\r\n<p>He flies ___ kite in the wind. - his</p>\r\n<p>I see ___ footprints in the sand. - my</p>', 1, 5, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:31:46', '2019-07-25 21:40:44'),
(113, 5, 16, 1, 'The Simple Past Tense', 'the-simple-past-tense', NULL, '<p>The simple past is used to describe an action that happened in the recent past.&nbsp; Follow these rules to create the simple past tense with regular verbs.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add -ed to the simple form of the verb.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Visit</strong></p>\r\n<p>I visited</p>\r\n<p>you visited</p>\r\n<p>he visited</p>\r\n<p>she visited</p>\r\n<p>it visited</p>\r\n<p>we visited</p>\r\n<p>they visited</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add only -d if the verb ends in e.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Believe</strong></p>\r\n<p>I believed</p>\r\n<p>you believed</p>\r\n<p>he believed</p>\r\n<p>she believed</p>\r\n<p>it believed</p>\r\n<p>we believed</p>\r\n<p>they believed</p>\r\n<p><strong>Delete y and add -ied if the verb ends in y preceded by a consonant.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Cry</strong></p>\r\n<p>I cried</p>\r\n<p>you cried</p>\r\n<p>he cried</p>\r\n<p>she cried</p>\r\n<p>it cried</p>\r\n<p>we cried</p>\r\n<p>they cried</p>\r\n<h3>Pronunciation</h3>\r\n<p><strong>When -ed is added to verb that end in d, pronounce the last syllable separately.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Need</strong></p>\r\n<p>I need-ed</p>\r\n<p>you need-ed</p>\r\n<p>he need-ed</p>\r\n<p>she need-ed</p>\r\n<p>it need-ed</p>\r\n<p>we need-ed</p>\r\n<p>they need-ed</p>\r\n<p><strong>When -ed is added to verbs that end in t, pronounce the last syllable separately.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Want</strong></p>\r\n<p>I want-ed</p>\r\n<p>you want-ed</p>\r\n<p>he want-ed</p>\r\n<p>she want-ed</p>\r\n<p>it want-ed</p>\r\n<p>we want-ed</p>\r\n<p>they want-ed</p>\r\n<p><strong>The ending of all other regular verbs is pronounced as one syllable when -ed is added.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Open</strong></p>\r\n<p>I opened</p>\r\n<p>you opened</p>\r\n<p>he opened</p>\r\n<p>she opened</p>\r\n<p>it opened</p>\r\n<p>we opened</p>\r\n<p>they opened</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:42:18', '2019-07-25 22:16:06'),
(114, 5, 16, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to answer</p>\r\n<p>to increase</p>\r\n<p>to share</p>\r\n<p>to kill</p>\r\n<p>to try</p>\r\n<p>to lie</p>\r\n<p>to reward</p>\r\n<p>to notice</p>\r\n<p>to land</p>\r\n<p>to dry</p>\r\n<p>to sign</p>\r\n<p>to challenge</p>\r\n<p>hair dryer</p>\r\n<p>upside down</p>\r\n<p>snack</p>\r\n<p>lease</p>\r\n<p>age</p>\r\n<p>ditch</p>\r\n<p>inside out</p>\r\n<p>another</p>\r\n<p>eel</p>\r\n<p>toad</p>\r\n<p>building</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:52:12', '2019-07-25 21:53:34'),
(115, 5, 16, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the simple past tense by adding -ed or -ied to the simple form of the verb in parenthesis.</p>\r\n<p>I (to use) my hair dryer to dry my hair. - used</p>\r\n<p>We (to try) a new recipe last night. - tried</p>\r\n<p>Thomas (to answer) the phone. - answered</p>\r\n<p>I (to notice) that your sweated was inside out. - noticed</p>\r\n<p>The car (to land) upside down in the ditch. - landed</p>\r\n<p>She (to share) her snack with her friends at school yesterday. - shared</p>\r\n<p>The minimum wage (to increase) last year. - increased</p>\r\n<p>Suzanne (to lie) about her age. - lied</p>\r\n<p>My company (to sign) the lease for our building for another three years - signed</p>\r\n<p>The teacher (to challenge) her students to work hard. - challenged</p>\r\n<p>The snake (to kill) the frog. - killed</p>', 1, 30, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:53:49', '2019-07-25 22:55:23'),
(116, 5, 16, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>to destry</p>\r\n<p>to describe</p>\r\n<p>to rain</p>\r\n<p>to knock</p>\r\n<p>to borrow</p>\r\n<p>to avoid</p>\r\n<p>to move</p>\r\n<p>to tidy</p>\r\n<p>to decide</p>\r\n<p>to obtain</p>\r\n<p>to please</p>\r\n<p>to expect</p>\r\n<p>to serve</p>\r\n<p>to deny</p>\r\n<p>to accept</p>\r\n<p>to marry</p>\r\n<p>to arrest</p>\r\n<p>to prove</p>\r\n<p>to join</p>\r\n<p>to paint</p>\r\n<p>in-line skates</p>\r\n<p>contract</p>\r\n<p>lawn</p>\r\n<p>accident</p>\r\n<p>everybody</p>\r\n<p>in detail</p>\r\n<p>someone</p>\r\n<p>weekend</p>\r\n<p>terms</p>\r\n<p>audience</p>\r\n<p>innocent</p>\r\n<p>plain</p>\r\n<p>army</p>\r\n<p>door</p>\r\n<p>makeup</p>\r\n<p>collision</p>\r\n<p>doctor</p>\r\n<p>conditions</p>\r\n<p>passport</p>\r\n<p>court</p>\r\n<p>alert</p>\r\n<p>appetizer</p>\r\n<p>singer</p>\r\n<p>police</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 22:02:22', '2019-07-25 22:04:24'),
(117, 5, 16, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the sentences using the simple past tense by adding <strong>-ed</strong> or <strong>-ied</strong> to the simple form of these regular verbs.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to accept) the terms and conditions of the contract. - accepted</p>\r\n<p>My brother ___ (to join) the army. - joined</p>\r\n<p>My neighbors ___ (to move) to Vancouver. - moved</p>\r\n<p>Someone ___ (to knock) on the door. - knocked</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to describe) the accident in detail. - described</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to prove) that I was innocent in court. - proved</p>\r\n<p>The man ___ (to deny) everything. - denied</p>\r\n<p>Tina ___ (to borrow) my in-line skates. - borrowed</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (to watch) the kids in the pool. - watched</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to use) my makeup. - used</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to tidy) the house for my mother. - tidied</p>\r\n<p>It ___ (to rain) all day. - rained</p>\r\n<p>My husband ___ (to paint) the bathroom on the weekend. - painted</p>\r\n<p>I was alert and I ___ (to avoid) the collision. - avoided</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to push) the baby in the carriage. - pushed</p>\r\n<p>My cousin ___ (to marry) a doctor. - married</p>\r\n<p>The singer ___ (to please) the audience. - pleased</p>\r\n<p>Your dog ___ (to destory) my lawn. - destroyed</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to serve) appetizers to our guests. - served</p>\r\n<p>Mike ___ (to obtain) his passport. - obtained</p>\r\n<p>The police ___ (to arrest) everybody. - arrested</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to order) a plain pizza last night. - ordered</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to decide) to learn English. - decided</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to expect) to see you there. - expected</p>', 1, 30, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 22:04:41', '2019-07-25 22:57:23'),
(119, 5, 17, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>felt (to feel)</p>\r\n<p>bit (to bite)</p>\r\n<p>blew (to blow)</p>\r\n<p>shook (to shake)</p>\r\n<p>tore (to tear)</p>\r\n<p>slid (to slide)</p>\r\n<p>spent (to spend)</p>\r\n<p>taught (to teach)</p>\r\n<p>did (to do)</p>\r\n<p>found (to find)</p>\r\n<p>fell (to fall)</p>\r\n<p>cut (to cut)</p>\r\n<p>broke (to break)</p>\r\n<p>bought (to buy)</p>\r\n<p>took (to take)</p>\r\n<p>honeymoon</p>\r\n<p>earthquake</p>\r\n<p>grandparent</p>\r\n<p>toboggan</p>\r\n<p>Ireland</p>\r\n<p>finger</p>\r\n<p>mountain</p>\r\n<p>when</p>\r\n<p>pants</p>\r\n<p>math</p>\r\n<p>dishes</p>\r\n<p>saw</p>\r\n<p>cup</p>\r\n<p>overseas</p>\r\n<p>down</p>\r\n<p>favorite</p>\r\n<p>high school</p>\r\n<p>after</p>\r\n<p>gift</p>\r\n<p>ankle</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 00:03:27', '2019-07-26 00:06:36'),
(120, 5, 17, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the simple past tense using the irrgular past tense form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>She (to blow) on her soup because it was hot. - blew</p>\r\n<p>The house (to shake) a lot during the earthquake. - shook</p>\r\n<p>They (to take) the plane for their honeymoon overseas. - took</p>\r\n<p>We (to spend) our time shopping. - spent</p>\r\n<p>I always (to feel) sick when I was pregnant. - felt</p>\r\n<p>He (to tear) his pants. - tore</p>\r\n<p>We (to buy) a nice gift for our grandparents. - bought</p>\r\n<p>The kids (to slide) down the mountain. - slid</p>\r\n<p>I (to do) the dishes after supper. - did</p>\r\n<p>I (to cut) my finger on the sharp saw. - cut</p>\r\n<p>You (to break) my favorite cup. - broke</p>\r\n<p>Your dog (to bite) my ankle. - bit</p>\r\n<p>Karen (to find) a purse at the beach. - found</p>\r\n<p>I (to teach) math at the high school last year. - taught</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 00:06:54', '2019-07-26 00:12:01'),
(121, 5, 17, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>spoke (to speak)</p>\r\n<p>held (to hold)</p>\r\n<p>paid (to pay)</p>\r\n<p>stole (to steal)</p>\r\n<p>hung (to hang)</p>\r\n<p>shot (to shoot)</p>\r\n<p>began (to begin)</p>\r\n<p>dugg&nbsp; (to dig)</p>\r\n<p>drew (to draw)</p>\r\n<p>left (to leave)</p>\r\n<p>swore (to swear)</p>\r\n<p>sat (to sit)</p>\r\n<p>heard (to hear)</p>\r\n<p>saw (to see)</p>\r\n<p>gave (to give)</p>\r\n<p>niece</p>\r\n<p>front</p>\r\n<p>store</p>\r\n<p>whistle</p>\r\n<p>thing</p>\r\n<p>pantry</p>\r\n<p>bored</p>\r\n<p>witch</p>\r\n<p>plastic</p>\r\n<p>broom</p>\r\n<p>great</p>\r\n<p>swing</p>\r\n<p>speech</p>\r\n<p>calculator</p>\r\n<p>problem</p>\r\n<p>tunnel</p>\r\n<p>midnight</p>\r\n<p>party</p>\r\n<p>stop sign</p>\r\n<p>shoplifter</p>\r\n<p>crossing guard</p>\r\n<p>pink flamingo</p>\r\n<p>nephew</p>\r\n<p>underground</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:15:26', '2019-07-26 01:18:33'),
(122, 5, 17, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences in the simple past tense using the irregular past tense form of the verb indicated in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>The teachers ___ (to speak) about the computer problems. - spoke</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to begin) my homework after school. - began</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to give) money to his neice. - gave</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to hang) the whistle around he neck. - hung</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to see) the shoplifter in the store. - saw</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to sit) on the swing and talked. - sat</p>\r\n<p>Somebody ___ (to steal) my pencil at school. - stole</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to pay) a lot of money for the book. - paid</p>\r\n<p>Cheyenne ___ (to draw) a nice picture of a tree. - drew</p>\r\n<p>David ___ (to swear) in class today. - swore</p>\r\n<p>The workers ___ (to dig) a big tunnel. - dug</p>\r\n<p>The crossing guard ___ (to hold) the stop sign. - held</p>\r\n<p>The police ___ (to shoot) the man in the leg. - shot</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to hear) your speech last night. - heard</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (to leave) the party late. - left</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to see) a mouse. - saw</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:19:26', '2019-07-26 01:24:17'),
(123, 5, 18, 1, 'The Simple Past Tense with Irregular Verbs: 2', 'the-simple-past-tense-with-irregular-verbs--2', NULL, '<p>Some verbs do not use the <strong>-ed</strong> ending to express the past tense.&nbsp; These are irregular verbs, and they have unique past tense forms.&nbsp; They have the same form for all persons in the past tense, and they must be memorized.</p>\r\n<p>To Have (had)</p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they had</p>\r\n<p>To Lend (lent)</p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they lent</p>\r\n<p>To Drive (drove)</p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they drove</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:32:18', '2019-07-26 01:34:39');
