(124, 5, 18, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>had (to have)</p>\r\n<p>lent (to lend)</p>\r\n<p>drove (to drive)</p>\r\n<p>came (to come)</p>\r\n<p>woke (to wake)</p>\r\n<p>built (to build)</p>\r\n<p>forgot (to forget)</p>\r\n<p>froze (to freeze)</p>\r\n<p>caught (to catch)</p>\r\n<p>beat (to beat)</p>\r\n<p>rode (to ride)</p>\r\n<p>bent (to bend)</p>\r\n<p>slept (to sleep)</p>\r\n<p>understood (to understand)</p>\r\n<p>withdrew (to withdraw)</p>\r\n<p>bacon</p>\r\n<p>stamp</p>\r\n<p>rifle</p>\r\n<p>sheep</p>\r\n<p>hay</p>\r\n<p>first</p>\r\n<p>lunch</p>\r\n<p>barn</p>\r\n<p>cheese</p>\r\n<p>bullfrog</p>\r\n<p>hanger</p>\r\n<p>hunter</p>\r\n<p>lamb</p>\r\n<p>bagel</p>\r\n<p>month</p>\r\n<p>whole</p>\r\n<p>enough</p>\r\n<p>tadpole</p>\r\n<p>envelope</p>\r\n<p>post office</p>\r\n<p>sand castle</p>\r\n<p>warehouse</p>\r\n<p>inventory</p>\r\n<p>lettuce</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:34:51', '2019-07-26 01:37:42'),
(125, 5, 18, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentence in the simple past tense using the past tense form of the irregular verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to withdraw) enough money for the whole month. - withdrew</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to catch) a bullfrog and four tadpoles in the pond. - caught</p>\r\n<p>Salina ___ (to ride) a horse yesterday. - rode</p>\r\n<p>Robert ___ (to build) a huge sand castle on the beach. - built</p>\r\n<p>Brandon ___ (to bend) the hanger to open the car door. - bent</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to drive) my new car yesterday. - drove</p>\r\n<p>The hunter ___ (to forget) his rifle in the woods. - forgot</p>\r\n<p>You ___ (to wake) your grandmother when you knocked. - woke</p>\r\n<p>The sheep and lamb ___ (to sleep) on the hay in the barn. - slept</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to have) a bagel with bacon for lunch. - had</p>\r\n<p>Camilie ___ (to understand) what the teacher taught in class today. - understood</p>\r\n<p>My mother ___ (to freeze) the vegetables for the winter. - froze</p>\r\n<p>Dimitri ___ (to lend) the shovel to his neighbor. - lent</p>\r\n<p>The red team ___ (to beat) the blue team. - beat</p>\r\n<p>Laurent ___ (to come) to help us with the inventory in the warehouse. - came</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:37:51', '2019-07-26 01:43:37'),
(126, 5, 18, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>shut (to shut)</p>\r\n<p>brought (to bring)</p>\r\n<p>won (to win)</p>\r\n<p>sent (to send)</p>\r\n<p>chose (to choose)</p>\r\n<p>grew (to grow)</p>\r\n<p>cost (to cost)</p>\r\n<p>forgave (to forgive)</p>\r\n<p>kept (to keep)</p>\r\n<p>rose (to rise)</p>\r\n<p>meant (to mean)</p>\r\n<p>hurt (to hurt)</p>\r\n<p>put (to put)</p>\r\n<p>lost (to lose)</p>\r\n<p>thought (to think)</p>\r\n<p>package</p>\r\n<p>cookie</p>\r\n<p>early</p>\r\n<p>toe</p>\r\n<p>cauliflower</p>\r\n<p>gorgeous</p>\r\n<p>joke</p>\r\n<p>park</p>\r\n<p>nail</p>\r\n<p>screw</p>\r\n<p>weed</p>\r\n<p>cabbage</p>\r\n<p>bride</p>\r\n<p>gardener</p>\r\n<p>hearing aid</p>\r\n<p>deaf</p>\r\n<p>hand</p>\r\n<p>airmail</p>\r\n<p>umbrella</p>\r\n<p>blind</p>\r\n<p>groom</p>\r\n<p>gift certificate</p>\r\n<p>even enough</p>\r\n<p>as</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:43:58', '2019-07-26 01:47:22'),
(127, 5, 18, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences in the simple past tense using the irregular past tense form of the verb indicated in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to bring) my umbrella when we went for a walk in the park. - brought</p>\r\n<p>It ___ (to cost) a lot but it was gorgeous and we loved it. - cost</p>\r\n<p>The sun ___ (to rise) early this morning. - rose</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to win) a gift certificate at the Christmas party. - won</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to grow) cabbages, cauliflowers, and pumpkins in our garden last summer. - grew</p>\r\n<p>The gardener ___ (to put) the weeds in the garbage can. - put</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to mean) that as a joke. - meant</p>\r\n<p>Jasmin ___ (to shut) the door on her toe. - shut</p>\r\n<p>The bride and groom ___ (to choose) a beautiful wedding cake. - chose</p>\r\n<p>Even though he lied, she ___ (to forgive) him. - forgave</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to think) you liked peas. - thought</p>\r\n<p>Sharon is blind and deaf and she ___ (to lose) her hearing aid.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ (to hurt) when the cat scratched my hand. - hurt</p>\r\n<p>My father ___ (to keep) the nails and screws in jars in the garage. - kept</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to send) the package by airmail. - sent</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to drink) milk with our cookies. - drank</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:47:31', '2019-07-26 01:52:42'),
(128, 5, 19, 1, 'The Simple Past Tense with Irregular Verbs: 3', 'the-simple-past-tense-with-irregular-verbs--3', NULL, '<p>Some verbs do not use the -ed ending to express the past tense.&nbsp; These are irregular verbs, and they have unique past tense forms.&nbsp; They have the same form for all persons in the past tense, and they must be memorized.</p>\r\n<p><strong>To Meet</strong> &rarr; <strong>met</strong></p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they <strong>met</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Sing</strong> &rarr; <strong>sang</strong></p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they <strong>sang</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Ring</strong> &rarr; <strong>rang</strong></p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they <strong>rang</strong></p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:08:12', '2019-07-26 02:11:31'),
(129, 5, 19, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to meet &rarr; met</p>\r\n<p>to sing &rarr; sang</p>\r\n<p>to ring &rarr; rang</p>\r\n<p>to throw &rarr; threw</p>\r\n<p>to run &rarr; ran</p>\r\n<p>to get &rarr; got</p>\r\n<p>to know &rarr; knew</p>\r\n<p>to sell &rarr; sold</p>\r\n<p>to spin &rarr; spun</p>\r\n<p>to feed &rarr; fed</p>\r\n<p>to fight &rarr; fought</p>\r\n<p>to light &rarr; lit</p>\r\n<p>to eat &rarr; ate</p>\r\n<p>to fit &rarr; fit</p>\r\n<p>to read &rarr; read</p>\r\n<p>fire</p>\r\n<p>too</p>\r\n<p>ice</p>\r\n<p>guilty</p>\r\n<p>crime</p>\r\n<p>paper</p>\r\n<p>noisy</p>\r\n<p>parrot</p>\r\n<p>middle</p>\r\n<p>icing</p>\r\n<p>Monday</p>\r\n<p>Tuesday</p>\r\n<p>Wednesday</p>\r\n<p>Thursday</p>\r\n<p>Friday</p>\r\n<p>Saturday</p>\r\n<p>Sunday</p>\r\n<p>raise</p>\r\n<p>evening</p>\r\n<p>liquor store</p>\r\n<p>power failure</p>\r\n<p>out of control</p>\r\n<p>concert</p>\r\n<p>phone</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:11:58', '2019-07-26 02:15:19'),
(130, 5, 19, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the simple past tense using the irregular past tense form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to sing) on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday at the concert in Montreal. - sang</p>\r\n<p>The house was dark because of the power failure so we ___ (to light) the candles. - lit</p>\r\n<p>The car ___ (to spin) out of control on the ice. - spun</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to read) the newspaper in the evening on Saturday and Sunday. - read</p>\r\n<p>My son ___ (to fight) at school on Tuesday and Thursday last week. - fought</p>\r\n<p>The phone ___ (to ring) in the middle of the night. - rang</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to know) that he was guilty of the crime. - knew</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to meet) Sara at the liquor store. - met</p>\r\n<p>Sorry, but I ___ (to eat) all the icing on your cake when you went to the bathroom. - ate</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to get) a big raise at work last month. - got</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to sell) our parrot because he was too noisy. - sold</p>\r\n<p>Alexandre ___ (to throw) the papers in the fire. - threw</p>\r\n<p>My pants ___ (to fit) last year. - fit</p>\r\n<p>Carmen ___ (to run) and hid under the bed. - ran</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to feed) meat to the fox. - fed</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:15:32', '2019-07-26 02:20:47'),
(131, 5, 19, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to swim &rarr; swam</p>\r\n<p>to say &rarr; said</p>\r\n<p>to tell &rarr; told</p>\r\n<p>to hit &rarr; hit</p>\r\n<p>to stick &rarr; stuck</p>\r\n<p>to lead &rarr; led</p>\r\n<p>to fly &rarr; flew</p>\r\n<p>to weep &rarr; wept</p>\r\n<p>to write &rarr; wrote</p>\r\n<p>to sweep &rarr; swept</p>\r\n<p>to stand &rarr; stood</p>\r\n<p>to deal &rarr; dealt</p>\r\n<p>to make &rarr; made</p>\r\n<p>to quit &rarr; quit</p>\r\n<p>to become &rarr; became</p>\r\n<p>sidewalk</p>\r\n<p>dentures</p>\r\n<p>wall</p>\r\n<p>date</p>\r\n<p>snowman</p>\r\n<p>minute</p>\r\n<p>corner</p>\r\n<p>chalk</p>\r\n<p>piece</p>\r\n<p>blackboard</p>\r\n<p>glue</p>\r\n<p>dolphine</p>\r\n<p>issue</p>\r\n<p>truth</p>\r\n<p>stream</p>\r\n<p>prnicess</p>\r\n<p>jury</p>\r\n<p>drink</p>\r\n<p>housecoat</p>\r\n<p>on vacation</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:21:14', '2019-07-26 02:23:56'),
(132, 5, 19, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences in the simple past tense using the irregular past tense form of the verb indicated in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to deal) with many issues at work yesterday. - dealt</p>\r\n<p>I thought you ___ (to say) it was free. - said</p>\r\n<p>Liliane ___ (to sweep) the sidewalk with her new broom. - swept</p>\r\n<p>The kindergarten class ___ (to make) a snowman this morning. - made</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to stick) the pieces of wood together with glue. - stuck</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to hit) my head on the wall when I fell down the stairs. - hit</p>\r\n<p>My father ___ (to become) angry when I quit school last year. - became</p>\r\n<p>My grandmother ___ (to wear) her dentures for her date with Mr. Olsen. - wore</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to lead) my horse to the stream for a drink of cold water. - led</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to fly) the kite in the field all day. - flew</p>\r\n<p>The teacher ___ (to write) on the blackboard with pink chalk. - wrote</p>\r\n<p>Emy and Meghan ___ (to swim) with dolphins when they were on vacation in Florida. - swam</p>\r\n<p>The princess ___ (to weep) alone in her room. - wept</p>\r\n<p>She says that she ___ (to tell) the truth to the jury. - told</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to stand) on the corner in the rain and waited for you for twenty minutes. - stood</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to give) me a housecoat and a puppy for my birthday. - gave</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:24:11', '2019-07-26 02:30:14'),
(133, 5, 20, 1, 'The Simple Past Tense: Negative Form', 'the-simple-past-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>did not</strong> after the subject and use the simple form of the verb to create the negative form of the simple past tense for regular and irregular verbs.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I did not break</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I did not break the cup.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you did not answer</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You did not answer me.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he did not believe</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He did not believe you.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she did not pass</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She did not pass her test.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it did not jump</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It did not jump on me.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we did not sell</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We did not sell our house.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they did not touch</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They did not touch it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the simple past tense can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>didn\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I did not boil</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I didn\'t boil</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I didn\'t boil the eggs.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you did not build</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you didn\'t build</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You didn\'t build your house.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he did not want</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he didn\'t want</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He didn\'t want coffee.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she did not do</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she didn\'t do</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She didn\'t do her homework.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it did not cost</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it didn\'t cost</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It didn\'t cost a lot.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we did not sign</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we didn\'t sign</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We didn\'t sign it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they did not find</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they didn\'t find</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They didn\'t find their cat.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:31:01', '2019-07-26 02:53:05'),
(134, 5, 20, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to shave</p>\r\n<p>to waste</p>\r\n<p>to apologize</p>\r\n<p>to report</p>\r\n<p>bottle</p>\r\n<p>screen</p>\r\n<p>skin</p>\r\n<p>income</p>\r\n<p>medicine</p>\r\n<p>valuable</p>\r\n<p>mussels</p>\r\n<p>clam</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:53:45', '2019-07-26 02:54:55'),
(135, 5, 20, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to express the negative form of the simple past tense.&nbsp; Write the sentence once using did not and once using didn\'t.</p>\r\n<p>They watched the hockey game on their new big screen TV.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>I forgot to tell him.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>She wasted my valuable time.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>Marcia reported her income.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>I shook the bottle of medicine.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>My uncle shaved his head.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>He apologized to his friend.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>We found clams and mussels in the sand on the beach.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>The police read the man his rights.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>It scratched my skin.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:55:07', '2019-07-26 02:58:52'),
(136, 5, 20, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to translate</p>\r\n<p>to deposit</p>\r\n<p>to gain</p>\r\n<p>to last</p>\r\n<p>to prevent</p>\r\n<p>to express</p>\r\n<p>to brush</p>\r\n<p>to save</p>\r\n<p>inch</p>\r\n<p>wallet</p>\r\n<p>hat</p>\r\n<p>shower</p>\r\n<p>upstairs</p>\r\n<p>pay</p>\r\n<p>trip</p>\r\n<p>litter box</p>\r\n<p>Greece</p>\r\n<p>leftovers</p>\r\n<p>opinion</p>\r\n<p>mitten</p>\r\n<p>antenna</p>\r\n<p>pipe</p>\r\n<p>grandson</p>\r\n<p>granddaughter</p>\r\n<p>savings account</p>\r\n<p>pantyhose</p>\r\n<p>horoscope</p>\r\n<p>plumber</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:59:11', '2019-07-26 03:00:42'),
(137, 5, 20, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the negative form using the contraction <strong>didn\'t</strong> and the simple form of the verb.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (prevented) the accident. - didn\'t prevent</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (expressed) her opinion. - didn\'t express</p>\r\n<p>The movie ___ (lasted) three hours. - didn\'t last</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (went) to see their granddaughter and grandson. - didn\'t go</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (saved) a lot of money for their trip to Greece. - didn\'t save</p>\r\n<p>Patricia ___ (lost) her mittens, scarf, and hat at school. - didn\'t lose</p>\r\n<p>Sonia ___ (translated) the letter. - didn\'t translate</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (bought) a gift for her. - didn\'t buy</p>\r\n<p>Mario ___ (found) a black leather wallet in the snow. - didn\'t find</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (put) the leftovers in plastic bags. - didn\'t put</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (tore) my pantyhose. - didn\'t tear</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (knew) you were there. - didn\'t know</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (deposited) his pay in his savings account. - didn\'t deposit</p>\r\n<p>The plumber ___ (fixed) the pipes, shower, and toilet in the bathroom upstairs. - didn\'t fix</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (cleaned) the litter box this morning. - didn\'t clean</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (read) my horoscope today. - didn\'t read</p>\r\n<p>The wind ___ (bent) the antenna. - didn\'t bend</p>\r\n<p>Laura ___ (grew) two inches last year. - didn\'t grow</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (gained) ten punds. - didn\'t gain.</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (brushed) the cat yesterday. - didn\'t brush</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 03:01:01', '2019-07-26 03:09:11'),
(138, 5, 21, 1, 'The Simple Past Tense: Question Form', 'the-simple-past-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place did before the subject to create questions in the simple past tense.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb is always used when creating questions in the simple past tense with regular and irregular verbs.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did I eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did I eat your sandwich?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did you eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did you eat my last cookie?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did he eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did he eat his dessert?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did she eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did she eat the vegetables?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did it eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did it eat the egg?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did we eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did we eat everything?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did they eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did they eat the meat?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 03:58:59', '2019-07-26 04:02:30'),
(139, 5, 21, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>to weigh</p>\r\n<p>to elect</p>\r\n<p>to escape</p>\r\n<p>to change</p>\r\n<p>to cheat</p>\r\n<p>to offend</p>\r\n<p>to indicate</p>\r\n<p>to remain</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:03:02', '2019-07-26 04:03:31'),
(140, 5, 21, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions in the simple past tense by placing <strong>did</strong> before the subject and using the simple form of the verb.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n<p>You saw the beautiful rainbow. &rarr; Did you see the beautiful rainbow?</p>\r\n<p>He offended your when he said that. &rarr; Did he offend you when he said that?</p>\r\n<p>Exercises:</p>\r\n<p>Jessica found a starfish on the beach. - Did Jessica find a starfish on the beach?</p>\r\n<p>The squirrel ate the peanuts. - Did the squirrel eat the peanuts?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:03:49', '2019-07-26 04:07:10'),
(141, 5, 21, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>to load</p>\r\n<p>to lock</p>\r\n<p>to pick</p>\r\n<p>to ask</p>\r\n<p>to appear</p>\r\n<p>to attend</p>\r\n<p>to convince</p>\r\n<p>to climb</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:07:28', '2019-07-26 04:07:51'),
(142, 5, 21, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following setences using <strong>did</strong> and the simple form of the verb to create questions in the simple past tense.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>You took a picture of the sunset. - Did you take a picture of the sunset?</p>\r\n<p>She locked the safe. - Did she lock the safe?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:07:58', '2019-07-26 04:09:41'),
(143, 5, 22, 1, 'Prepositions: In and On', 'prepositions--in-and-on', NULL, '<h3>Use <strong>in</strong> as a preposition to indicate:</h3>\r\n<p><strong>the position or location:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The towels are in the dryer.</p>\r\n<p><strong>the year of the occurrence:</strong></p>\r\n<p>We married in 2003.</p>\r\n<p><strong>the months and seasons:</strong></p>\r\n<p>My flower garden is beautiful in the summer.</p>\r\n<p>It\'s my birthday in April.</p>\r\n<p><strong>points of the day (except for at night):</strong></p>\r\n<p>He left in the afternoon.</p>\r\n<p>He sleeps at night.</p>\r\n<p>He goes in the morning.</p>\r\n<p><strong>location within countries, cities, states, and provinces:</strong></p>\r\n<p>She goes to school in Montreal.</p>\r\n<p>He lives in Ohio.</p>\r\n<p>We had fun in Mexico.</p>\r\n<p>I met him in British Columbia.</p>\r\n<h3>Use on as a preposition to indicate:</h3>\r\n<p><strong>an object supported by a top surface:</strong></p>\r\n<p>the cup is on the table</p>\r\n<p><strong>the directional position of something:</strong></p>\r\n<p>It\'s the first door on the left.</p>\r\n<p><strong>a time of occurrence:</strong></p>\r\n<p>I worked on the weekend.</p>\r\n<p>She was sick on Friday.</p>\r\n<p><strong>a method of transportation (exception: in the car)</strong></p>\r\n<p>I felt sick on the plane.</p>\r\n<p>I felt sick in the car.</p>\r\n<p><strong>the mean of expression:</strong></p>\r\n<p>We talked on the phone for two hours.</p>\r\n<p>They played the song on the radio.</p>\r\n<p>I watched it on TV last week.</p>\r\n<p><strong>the subject of study:</strong></p>\r\n<p>I have a good book on horses.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:10:52', '2019-07-26 19:45:37'),
(144, 5, 22, 2, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences correctly by choosing <strong>in</strong> or <strong>on</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The garbage can is (in, on) the garage. - in</p>\r\n<p>Do you see signs of life (in, on) the moon? - on</p>\r\n<p>We will talk about it (in, on) the morning. - in</p>\r\n<p>We spent five days (in, on) Paris. - in</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:19:10', '2019-07-26 04:20:51'),
(145, 5, 22, 3, 'Vocabulary 1', 'vocabulary-1', NULL, '<p>economy</p>\r\n<p>blister</p>\r\n<p>wart</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:21:06', '2019-07-26 04:21:17'),
(146, 5, 22, 4, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences with in or on.</p>\r\n<p>They saw you [in, on] TV last night. - on</p>\r\n<p>My aunt died [in, on] August. - in</p>\r\n<p>She lives [in, on] the city. - in</p>\r\n<p>The people are [in, on] the ship. - on</p>\r\n<p>It\'s garbage day [in, on] Thursday. - on</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:21:24', '2019-07-26 04:23:01'),
(147, 5, 23, 1, 'There Is and There Are: Present Tense', 'there-is-and-there-are--present-tense', NULL, '<p>Use <strong>there is</strong> and <strong>there are</strong> to show that something exists.&nbsp; Use <strong>there is</strong> with singular nouns and <strong>there are</strong> with plural nouns.</p>\r\n<p>Singular</p>\r\n<p>There is a gift for you on the table</p>\r\n<p>There is a sand castle on the beach.</p>\r\n<p>There is a dove on the fence.</p>\r\n<p>There is a button on the floor.</p>\r\n<p>Plural</p>\r\n<p>There are two gifts for you on the table.</p>\r\n<p>There are a lot of sand castles on the beach.</p>\r\n<p>There are many doves on the fence.</p>\r\n<p>There are three buttons on the floor.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:23:30', '2019-07-26 04:26:20'),
(148, 5, 23, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:26:52', '2019-07-26 04:26:52'),
(149, 5, 23, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences by choosing <strong>there is</strong> or <strong>there are</strong> depending on whether the noun is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>[There is, There are] many meatballs and red peppers in the sauce. - There are</p>\r\n<p>[There is, There are] a whiteboard in my classroom. - There is</p>\r\n<p>[There is, There are] rocks in my boot. - There are</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:27:13', '2019-07-26 04:29:05'),
(150, 5, 23, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:29:21', '2019-07-26 04:29:21'),
(151, 5, 23, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences with <strong>is</strong> or <strong>are</strong> depending on whether the noun directly following the verb is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>There [is, are] many stars in the sky. - are</p>\r\n<p>There [is, are] a beehive in the garage. - is</p>\r\n<p>There [is, are] enough proof. - is</p>\r\n<p>There [is, are] a big roller coaster over there. - is</p>\r\n<p>There [is, are] two houses on this street. - are</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:29:31', '2019-07-26 04:31:46'),
(152, 5, 24, 1, 'Ther Is and There Are: Present Tense: Negative Form', 'ther-is-and-there-are--present-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place not after <strong>there is</strong> and <strong>there are</strong> to create a negative sentence.</p>\r\n<p>there is &rarr; there is not &rarr; There is not a rocking chair downstairs.</p>\r\n<p>there are &rarr; there are not &rarr; There are not many blankets on my bed.</p>\r\n<p>The negative form of <strong>there is</strong> and <strong>there are</strong> can also be expressed with the contractions <strong>there isn\'t</strong> and <strong>there aren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>there is not &rarr; there isn\'t &rarr; There isn\'t a bug in the house.</p>\r\n<p>there are not &rarr; there aren\'t &rarr; There aren\'t many leftovers.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:32:22', '2019-07-26 04:35:50'),
(153, 5, 24, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:36:09', '2019-07-26 04:36:09'),
(154, 5, 24, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to express the negative form of there is and there are.&nbsp; Write the sentence once using <strong>is not</strong> and <strong>are not</strong> and once using the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>There is a lot of shade in the backyard.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>There are two yellow folders on my desk.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:36:17', '2019-07-26 04:38:39'),
(155, 5, 24, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:38:57', '2019-07-26 04:38:57'),
(156, 5, 24, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Use the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong> to complete the following negative sentences.</p>\r\n<p>There [isn\'t, aren\'t] enough time. - isn\'t</p>\r\n<p>There [isn\'t, aren\'t] a pay phone in my school. - isn\'t</p>\r\n<p>There [isn\'t, aren\'t] two seats available for us. - aren\'t</p>\r\n<p>There [isn\'t, aren\'t] many people here. - aren\'t</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:39:05', '2019-07-26 04:41:34'),
(157, 5, 25, 1, 'There Is and There Are: Present Tense: Question Form', 'there-is-and-there-are--present-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>is</strong> or <strong>are</strong> before <strong>there</strong> to create questions in the present tense.</p>\r\n<p>there is &rarr; is there &rarr; Is there a kitten outside?</p>\r\n<p>there are &rarr; are there &rarr; Are there ducks in the pond?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:42:01', '2019-07-26 04:43:36'),
(158, 5, 25, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:43:48', '2019-07-26 04:43:48'),
(159, 5, 25, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions by placing <strong>is</strong> or <strong>are</strong> before <strong>there</strong>.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>There is a vending machine in the cafeteria. - Is there a vending machine in the cafetieria?</p>\r\n<p>There are enough life jackets in the boat. - Are there enough life jackets in the boat?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:44:35', '2019-07-26 04:46:25'),
(160, 5, 25, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:46:38', '2019-07-26 04:46:38'),
(161, 5, 25, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following questions with <strong>is</strong> or <strong>are</strong> depending on whether the noun directly referring to the verb is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>[is, are] there fingerprints on the gun? - are</p>\r\n<p>[is, are] there a pool table in the playroom? - is</p>\r\n<p>[is, are] there porcupines in the yard? - are</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:46:45', '2019-07-26 04:48:35'),
(162, 5, 26, 1, 'There Is and There Are: Past Tense', 'there-is-and-there-are--past-tense', NULL, '<p>The past tense of the singular <strong>there is</strong> is <strong>there was</strong> and the past tense of the plural <strong>there are</strong> is <strong>there were</strong>.&nbsp; Use <strong>there was</strong> and <strong>there were</strong> to show that something existed in the past.</p>\r\n<p>there is &rarr; there was &rarr; There was a loud noise downstairs last night.</p>\r\n<p>there are &rarr; there were &rarr; There were dark clouds in the sky.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:49:02', '2019-07-26 04:51:39'),
(163, 5, 26, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:52:00', '2019-07-26 04:52:00'),
(164, 5, 26, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following past tense sentences by choosing <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> depending on whether the noun directly following the verb is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] rust on the knife. - was</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] rules to follow. - were</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] a big sale at the mall, so I bought a scarf and shoes. - was</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] a CD player in my car but someone stole it. - was</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:52:09', '2019-07-26 04:54:08'),
(165, 5, 26, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:54:28', '2019-07-26 04:54:28'),
(166, 5, 26, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following past tense sentences using <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> depending on whether the noun directly following the verb is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] a new priest in my church today. - was</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] a lot of clothespins in the bag. - were</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] many houses for sale last year. - were</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] a rainbow after the storm. - was</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:54:53', '2019-07-26 04:56:47'),
(167, 5, 27, 1, 'There Is and There Are: Past Tense: Negative Form', 'there-is-and-there-are--past-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>not</strong> after <strong>there was</strong> and <strong>there were</strong> to create a negative sentence.</p>\r\n<p>there was &rarr; there was not &rarr; There was not a doll on the chair.</p>\r\n<p>there were &rarr; there were not &rarr; There were not many kids in the pool.</p>\r\n<p>The negative form of <strong>there was</strong> and <strong>there were</strong> can also be expressed with the contractions <strong>there wasn\'t</strong> and <strong>there weren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>there was not &rarr; there wasn\'t &rarr; There wasn\'t a bruise on his arm.</p>\r\n<p>there were not &rarr; there weren\'t &rarr; There weren\'t many fish in the lake.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:59:10', '2019-07-26 05:02:28'),
(168, 5, 27, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 05:02:42', '2019-07-26 05:02:42'),
(169, 5, 27, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to express the negative form.&nbsp; Write the sentence once using <strong>was not</strong> or <strong>were not</strong> and once using the contractions <strong>wasn\'t</strong> or <strong>weren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>There was a crack in my windshield. - There was not a crack in my windshield.</p>\r\n<p>There was a crack in my windshield. - There wasn\'t a crack in my windshield.</p>\r\n<p>There were many shells and stones in the sand on the beach. - There were not many ...</p>\r\n<p>There were many shells and stones in the sand on the beach. - There weren\'t many ...</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 05:02:52', '2019-07-26 05:05:25'),
(170, 5, 27, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 05:05:40', '2019-07-26 05:05:40'),
(171, 5, 27, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Use the contractions <strong>wasn\'t</strong> or <strong>weren\'t</strong> to complete the following negative sentences.</p>\r\n<p>There [wasn\'t, weren\'t] a bottle of mouthwash on the shelf in the bathroom. - wasn\'t</p>\r\n<p>There [wasn\'t, weren\'t] many chapters in the book. - weren\'t</p>\r\n<p>There [wasn\'t, weren\'t] a rope in the boat. - wasn\'t</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 05:05:47', '2019-07-26 05:07:19'),
(172, 5, 28, 1, 'There Is and There Are: Past Tense: Question Form', 'there-is-and-there-are--past-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> before <strong>there</strong> to create questions in the past tense.</p>\r\n<p>there was &rarr; was there &rarr; Was there a cushion on the chair?</p>\r\n<p>there were &rarr; were there &rarr; Were there enough snacks for the kids?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 06:59:30', '2019-07-26 07:00:57'),
(173, 5, 28, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:01:14', '2019-07-26 07:01:14'),
(174, 5, 28, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions by placing <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> before <strong>there</strong>.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>There were many knights to guard the castle in the kingdom. - Were there many knights...?</p>\r\n<p>There was a wooden outhouse behind our cottage in the country. - Was there a wooden outhouse...?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:01:23', '2019-07-26 07:03:17'),
(175, 5, 28, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:03:36', '2019-07-26 07:03:36'),
(176, 5, 28, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following past tense questions with <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> depending on whether the noun directly referring to the verb is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>[Was, Were] there dinosaurs on Earth? - were</p>\r\n<p>[Was, Were] there a cardboard box in the bedroom? - was</p>\r\n<p>[Was, Were] there a lock on the door? - was</p>\r\n<p>[Was, Were] there many pennies in the jar? - were</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:03:44', '2019-07-26 07:05:46'),
(177, 5, 29, 1, 'Prepositions: To and At', 'prepositions--to-and-at', NULL, '<p>Use <strong>to</strong> as a preposition to describe a movement or an action toward a person, place, or thing.</p>\r\n<p>I walk to school.</p>\r\n<p>She goes to the bank every week.</p>\r\n<p>Use <strong>at</strong> as a preposition to describe an action performed when a person or thing arrives at a location.</p>\r\n<p>We learn a lot at school.</p>\r\n<p>I hurt my knee at the playground.</p>\r\n<p>Use at as a preposition to refer to time.</p>\r\n<p>We have a meeting at three o\'clock.</p>\r\n<p>He eats breakfast at 7:30 A.M.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:06:12', '2019-07-26 07:08:39'),
(178, 5, 29, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:08:56', '2019-07-26 07:08:56'),
(179, 5, 29, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences correctly by choosing <strong>to</strong> or <strong>at</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Please explain [to, at] me. - to</p>\r\n<p>The girls ate cake [to, at] the birthday party. - at</p>\r\n<p>We saw Tony and his brother [to, at] the restaurant. - at</p>', 1, 40, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:09:04', '2019-07-26 19:30:25'),
(180, 5, 29, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:10:39', '2019-07-26 07:10:39'),
(181, 5, 29, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences with <strong>to</strong> or <strong>at</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>I forgot my homework [to, at] my house. - at</p>\r\n<p>They signed the contract [to, at] the courthouse. - at</p>\r\n<p>He sent a gift certificate [to, at] his mother. - to</p>\r\n<p>Throw it [to, at] me. - to</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:10:52', '2019-07-26 07:12:16'),
(256, 5, 45, 1, 'The Present Perfect Tense', 'the-present-perfect-tense', NULL, '<p>The present perfect tense is used when the time of a past activity is not important or is not known in the sentence.&nbsp; Use <strong>has</strong> or <strong>have</strong> and the past participle of the verb with both regular and irregular verbs to form the present perfect tense.</p>\r\n<p>Contactions can also be used with the pronouns to create the present perfect tense.</p>\r\n<p>Regular</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >SIMPLE PRESENT</td>\r\n<td >SIMPLE PAST</td>\r\n<td >PRESENT PREFECT</td>\r\n<td >CONTRACTION</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I work</td>\r\n<td >I worked</td>\r\n<td >I have worked</td>\r\n<td >I\'ve worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you work</td>\r\n<td >you worked</td>\r\n<td >you have worked</td>\r\n<td >you\'ve worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he works</td>\r\n<td >he worked</td>\r\n<td >he has worked</td>\r\n<td >he\'s worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she works</td>\r\n<td >she worked</td>\r\n<td >she has worked</td>\r\n<td >she\'s worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it works</td>\r\n<td >it worked</td>\r\n<td >it has worked</td>\r\n<td >it\'s worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we work</td>\r\n<td >we worked</td>\r\n<td >we have worked</td>\r\n<td >we\'ve worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they work</td>\r\n<td >they worked</td>\r\n<td >they have worked</td>\r\n<td >they\'ve worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Irregular</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >SIMPLE PRESENT</td>\r\n<td >SIMPLE PAST</td>\r\n<td >PRESENT PERFECT</td>\r\n<td >CONTRACTION</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I take</td>\r\n<td >I took</td>\r\n<td >I have taken</td>\r\n<td >I\'ve taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you take</td>\r\n<td >you took</td>\r\n<td >you have taken</td>\r\n<td >you\'ve taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he takes</td>\r\n<td >he took</td>\r\n<td >he has taken</td>\r\n<td >he\'s taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she takes</td>\r\n<td >she took</td>\r\n<td >she has taken</td>\r\n<td >she\'s taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it takes</td>\r\n<td >it took</td>\r\n<td >it has taken</td>\r\n<td >it\'s taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we take</td>\r\n<td >we took</td>\r\n<td >we have taken</td>\r\n<td >we\'ve taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they take</td>\r\n<td >they took</td>\r\n<td >they have taken</td>\r\n<td >they\'ve taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-29 02:53:24', '2019-07-29 03:00:52'),
(182, 5, 30, 1, 'The Present Progressing (Continuous) Tense', 'the-present-progressing--continuous--tense', NULL, '<p>The present progressive is used to describe an activity that is presently in progress.&nbsp; It is formed using the verb <strong>To Be</strong> and by adding <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I drink</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am drinking my milk with a straw.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you drink</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you are drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You are drinking my wine.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he drinks</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he is drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He is drinking a cold beer.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she drinks</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she is drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She is drinking a cup of tea.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it drinks</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it is drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It is drinking the water in the toilet.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we drink</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we are drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We are drinking orange juice.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they drink</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they are drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They are drinking grape juice.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 21:51:49', '2019-07-26 21:55:56'),
(183, 5, 30, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 21:56:14', '2019-07-26 21:56:14'),
(184, 5, 30, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the present progressive tense.&nbsp; Use the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong>, and add <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>The wolf (to howl) at the moon. - is howling</p>\r\n<p>Sheila (to worry) now because her daughter is late. - is worrying</p>\r\n<p>It is cold and we (to shiver). - are shivering</p>\r\n<p>They (to cross) the lake in a canoe. - are crossing</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 21:56:29', '2019-07-26 21:59:01'),
(185, 5, 30, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 21:59:27', '2019-07-26 21:59:27'),
(186, 5, 30, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences to form the present progressive tense.&nbsp; Use the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> and add <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to dress) the baby in the bedroom. - is dressing</p>\r\n<p>You ___ (to cough) a lot. - are coughing</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (to sit) in the dining room. - are sitting</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to leave) now. - am leaving</p>\r\n<p>Bob ___ (to send) a postcard. - is sending</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 21:59:36', '2019-07-26 22:03:03'),
(187, 5, 31, 1, 'The Present Progressive (Continuous) Tense: Negative Form', 'the-present-progressive--continuous--tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place not after the verb To Be to create the negative form of the present progressive tense.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not following you.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you are not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You are not following him.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he is not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He is not following a recipe.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she is not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She is not following the rules.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it is not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It is not following me.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we are not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We are not following the car.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they are not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They are not following us.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the present progressive tense can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.&nbsp; There is no contraction for <strong>am not</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not washing the floor.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you aren\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You aren\'t washing your hair.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he isn\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He isn\'t washing his hands.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she isn\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She isn\'t washing the dishes.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it isn\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It isn\'t washing its baby.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we aren\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We aren\'t washing our car.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they aren\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They aren\'t washing the dog.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:03:55', '2019-07-26 22:10:48'),
(188, 5, 31, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:11:04', '2019-07-26 22:11:04'),
(189, 5, 31, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the negative form of the present progressive tense.&nbsp; Write your answer once with <strong>am not</strong>, <strong>is not</strong> or <strong>are not</strong> and once with the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>He is shouting at you. - is not</p>\r\n<p>He is shouting at you. - isn\'t</p>\r\n<p>They are waiting downstairs for us. - are not</p>\r\n<p>They are waiting downstairs for us. - aren\'t</p>\r\n<p>I am teaching school this year. - am not</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:11:13', '2019-07-26 22:14:17'),
(190, 5, 31, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:14:30', '2019-07-26 22:14:30'),
(191, 5, 31, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Use <strong>am not</strong> or the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong> to complete the following sentences in the negative present progressive form.&nbsp; Add <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to joke) about that. - isn\'t</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (to pray) in the church. - aren\'t</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to make) cabbage rolls. - am not</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:14:37', '2019-07-26 22:16:45');
