(192, 5, 32, 1, 'The Present Progressive (Continuous) Tense: Question Form', 'the-present-progressive--continuous--tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place the verb To Be before the subject to create questions in the present progressive tense.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >am I watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Am I watching you?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >are you watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Are you watching the game?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >is he watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Is he watching the news?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >is she watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Is she watching the time?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >is it watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Is it watching me?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >are we watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Are we watching them?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >are they watching</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Are they watching the kids?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:17:29', '2019-07-26 22:19:51'),
(193, 5, 32, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:20:01', '2019-07-26 22:20:01'),
(194, 5, 32, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the question form of the present progressive tense by placing the verb <strong>To Be</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>They are talking about the newborn baby. - Are they talking?</p>\r\n<p>He is hunting with a bow and arrow. - Is he hunting?</p>\r\n<p>I am rocking the boat. - Are you rocking the boat?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:20:07', '2019-07-26 22:22:35'),
(195, 5, 32, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:22:44', '2019-07-26 22:22:44'),
(196, 5, 32, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions in the present progressive tense by placing the verb <strong>To Be</strong> before the subject.</p>\r\n<p>Tom is spying on us. - Is Tom spying on us?</p>\r\n<p>I am failing my science class. - Am I failing my science class?</p>\r\n<p>The children are bursting the balloons. - Are the children bursting the balloons?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:22:57', '2019-07-26 22:24:50'),
(197, 5, 33, 1, 'The Past Progressive (Continuous) Tense', 'the-past-progressive--continuous--tense', NULL, '<p>The past progressive is used to describe an activity that happened and continued for a period of time in the past.&nbsp; It is formed using the past tense of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> and by adding <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I was using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I was using the stove.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You were using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You were using my stapler.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He was using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He was using my car.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She was using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She was using my makeup.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It was using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It was using its paws.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We were using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We were using the glue.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They were using</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They were using the laptop.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:25:22', '2019-07-26 22:28:44'),
(198, 5, 33, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:28:54', '2019-07-26 22:28:54'),
(199, 5, 33, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to form the past progressive tense.&nbsp; Use the correct past tense form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> and add <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb in parenthesis.</p>\r\n<p>The laboratory (to test) the blood for AIDS and other diseases. - was testing</p>\r\n<p>We (to walk) in the snow with our snowshoes. - were walking</p>\r\n<p>I (to change) the lightbulb when I got a shock. - was changing</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:28:59', '2019-07-26 22:31:47'),
(200, 5, 33, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:31:57', '2019-07-26 22:31:57'),
(201, 5, 33, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences to form the past progressive tense.&nbsp; Use the correct past tense form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> and add <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>The flowers ___ (to bloom) in the garden. - were blooming</p>\r\n<p>Raul ___ (to eat) pork and beans. - was eating</p>\r\n<p>The eggs ___ (to hatch). - were hatching</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:32:03', '2019-07-26 22:34:17'),
(202, 5, 34, 1, 'The Past Progressive (Continuous) Tense: Negative Form', 'the-past-progressive--continuous--tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>not</strong> after the past tense form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> to create the negative form of the past progressive tense.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I was moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >I was not moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >I was not moving my leg.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you were moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >you were not moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >You were not moving it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he was moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >he was not moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >He was not moving his pen.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she was moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >she was not moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >She was not moving her lips.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it was moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >it was not moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >It was not moving its tail.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we were moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >we were not moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >We were not moving our car.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they were moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >they were not moving</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >They were not moving it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the past progressive tense can also be expressed with the contaction <strong>wasn\'t</strong> or <strong>weren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I was not helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >I wasn\'t helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >I wasn\'t helping him.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you were not helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >you weren\'t helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >You weren\'t helping me.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he was not helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >he wasn\'t helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >He wasn\'t helping his aunt.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she was not helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >she wasn\'t helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >She wasn\'t helping the nurse.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it was not helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >it wasn\'t helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >It wasn\'t helping us.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we were not helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >we weren\'t helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >We weren\'t helping her.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they were not helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >they weren\'t helping</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >They weren\'t helping them.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:34:50', '2019-07-26 22:40:31'),
(203, 5, 34, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:40:48', '2019-07-26 22:40:48'),
(204, 5, 34, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the negative form of the past progressive tense.&nbsp; Write your answer once with <strong>was not</strong> or <strong>were not</strong> and once with the contraction <strong>wasn\'t</strong> or <strong>weren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>She was getting treatments for cancer. - was not getting</p>\r\n<p>She was getting treatments for caner. - wasn\'t getting</p>\r\n<p>We were driving on the road. - were not driving</p>\r\n<p>We were driving on the road. - weren\'t driving</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:40:55', '2019-07-26 22:43:25'),
(205, 5, 34, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:43:35', '2019-07-26 22:43:35'),
(206, 5, 34, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences using the contraction <strong>wasn\'t</strong> or <strong>weren\'t</strong> to complete the following sentenses in the negative past progressive form.&nbsp; Add <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to snip) the black wire. - wasn\'t snipping</p>\r\n<p>You ___ (to overdo) it. - weren\'t overdoing</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to taste) your dessert. - wasn\'t tasting</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:43:42', '2019-07-26 22:46:19'),
(207, 5, 35, 1, 'The Past Progressive (Continuous) Tense: Question Form', 'the-past-progressive--continuous--tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place the past tense form of the verb To Be before the subject to create questions in the past progressive tense.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I was swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >was I swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Was I swimming well?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you were swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >were you swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Were you swimming alone?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he was swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >was he swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Was he swimming with you?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she was swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >was she swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Was she swimming at night?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it was swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >was it swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Was it swimming in the bath?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we were swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >were we swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Were you swimming better?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they were swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >were they swimming</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Were they swimming fast?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:47:03', '2019-07-26 22:49:44'),
(208, 5, 35, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:50:05', '2019-07-26 22:50:05'),
(209, 5, 35, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the question form of the past progressive tense by placing <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>The police were stopping everyone at the corner. - Were the police stopping?</p>\r\n<p>My rubber duck was floating in the bath. - Was my rubber duck floating?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:50:12', '2019-07-26 22:52:07'),
(210, 5, 35, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:52:16', '2019-07-26 22:52:16'),
(211, 5, 35, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions in the past progressive tense by placing <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>She was starting her car. - Was she starting her car?</p>\r\n<p>They were begging us to stay for supper. - Were they begging us?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:52:29', '2019-07-26 22:54:15'),
(212, 5, 36, 1, 'Prepositions: From and Of', 'prepositions--from-and-of', NULL, '<p>Use <strong>from</strong> as a preposition to:</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate a starting point of a movement</strong></p>\r\n<p>We drove from Montreal to Toronto.</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate a starting point of an action</strong></p>\r\n<p>My husband called me from work.</p>\r\n<p><strong>measure between points</strong></p>\r\n<p>I work from 8:00 A.M. to 4:00 P.M.</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate the source</strong></p>\r\n<p>She got the information from John.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Use <strong>of</strong> as a preposition to:</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate the cause or reason of an action</strong></p>\r\n<p>He died of a heart attack.</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate belonging</strong></p>\r\n<p>I met the queen of England.</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate the contents</strong></p>\r\n<p>I drank two cups of coffee this morning.</p>\r\n<p><strong>describe a characteristic of a person</strong></p>\r\n<p>He is a man of great courage.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:01:45', '2019-07-27 04:07:09'),
(213, 5, 36, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:07:33', '2019-07-27 04:07:33'),
(214, 5, 36, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences correctly by choosing <strong>from</strong> or <strong>at</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>We gave her a bouquet [from, of] flowers. - of</p>\r\n<p>I got a toothbrush [from, of] my dentist. - from</p>\r\n<p>He is a member [from, of] the hockey team. - of</p>\r\n<p>She sent me a postcard [from, of] Canada. - from</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:07:41', '2019-07-27 04:09:43'),
(215, 5, 36, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:10:05', '2019-07-27 04:10:05'),
(216, 5, 36, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences with <strong>from</strong> or <strong>of</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>She bought a basket [from, of] fruit for us. - of</p>\r\n<p>He is a man [from, of] experience. - of</p>\r\n<p>Are you [from, of] Montreal? - from</p>\r\n<p>The odor is coming [from, of] the refrigerator. - from</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:10:16', '2019-07-27 04:11:46'),
(217, 5, 37, 1, 'Will: Future Tense', 'will--future-tense', NULL, '<p>Use <strong>will</strong> to create the future tense for all persons.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb always follows <strong>will</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I will hold your books.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You will hold the baby.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He will hold my hand.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She will hold her doll.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It will hold the ball.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We will hold our fishing rods.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They will hold the ladder.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:12:14', '2019-07-27 04:15:05'),
(218, 5, 37, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:15:30', '2019-07-27 04:15:30'),
(219, 5, 37, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', 'Rewrite the following sentences in the future tense by using will and the simple form of the verb in parentheses.', '<p>I (to climb) to the top of the lighthouse to see the ships. - will climb</p>\r\n<p>You (to become) a rich and famous author. - will become</p>\r\n<p>The government (to reduce) taxes next year. - will reduce</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:16:09', '2019-07-27 04:17:22'),
(220, 5, 37, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:17:36', '2019-07-27 04:17:36'),
(221, 5, 37, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', 'Complete the sentences using will and the simple form of the verb in parentheses to create the future tense.', '<p>Brian (to calculate) his pay. - Brian will calculate his pay.</p>\r\n<p>We (to balance) our budget. - We will balance our budget.</p>\r\n<p>I (to miss) you. - I will miss you.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:18:20', '2019-07-27 04:20:02'),
(222, 5, 38, 1, 'Will: Future Tense: Negative Form', 'will--future-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>not</strong> after <strong>will</strong> to create the negative form of the future tense.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb always follows <strong>will not</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I will not be there.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You will not say that.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He will not pay me.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She will not see you.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It will not eat.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We will not borrow money.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You will not drive to New York.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the future tense with <strong>will</strong> can be expressed with the contraction <strong>won\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I won\'t go.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You won\'t convince her.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He won\'t know.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She won\'t sleep late.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It won\'t bite you.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We won\'t spend a lot.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They won\'t help us.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:20:35', '2019-07-27 04:26:08'),
(223, 5, 38, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:26:36', '2019-07-27 04:26:36'),
(224, 5, 38, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the negative form of the future tense.&nbsp; Write your answer once with <strong>will not</strong> and once with the contraction <strong>won\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>He will declare bankruptcy. - He will not declare bankruptcy.</p>\r\n<p>He will declare bankruptcy. - He won\'t declare bankruptcy.</p>\r\n<p>The man will confess to the murder. - The man will not confess to the murder.</p>\r\n<p>The man will confess to the murder. - The man won\'t confess to the murder.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:26:45', '2019-07-27 04:29:02'),
(225, 5, 38, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:29:11', '2019-07-27 04:29:11'),
(226, 5, 38, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences by using the contraction <strong>won\'t</strong> and the simple form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ (to ruin) your reputation. - won\'t ruin</p>\r\n<p>It ___ (to clog) the drain. - won\'t clog</p>\r\n<p>My company ___ (to issue) the newsletter. - won\'t issue</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:29:18', '2019-07-27 04:30:55'),
(227, 5, 39, 1, 'Will: Future Tense: Question Form', 'will--future-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>will</strong> before the subject to create questions in the future tense.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb is always used when forming questions with <strong>will</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will I like</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will I like it?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will you call</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will you call me?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will he write</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will he write a book?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will she join</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will she join us for dinner?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will it annoy</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will it annoy you?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will we need</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will we need a new car?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will they worry</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will they worry about me?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:31:20', '2019-07-27 04:34:05'),
(228, 5, 39, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:34:17', '2019-07-27 04:34:17'),
(229, 5, 39, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the question form of the future tense by placing <strong>will</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>The snow will disappear in the spring. - Will the snow disappear in the spring?</p>\r\n<p>Your mother will punish you for that. - Will your mother punish you for that?</p>\r\n<p>The police will accuse Sara. - Will the police accuse Sara?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:34:29', '2019-07-27 04:36:32'),
(230, 5, 39, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:39:44', '2019-07-27 04:39:44'),
(231, 5, 39, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions in the future tense by placing <strong>will</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>It will arrive on time. - Will it arrive on time?</p>\r\n<p>He will publish his report. - Will he publish his report?</p>', 1, 30, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:40:02', '2019-07-27 04:42:15'),
(232, 2, 1, 2, 'Vocabulario Nuevo 2', 'vocabulario-nuevo-2', NULL, '<p>prisa o urgencia con que se hace algo - premura</p>\r\n<p>ruidoso, turbulento - estrepitoso</p>\r\n<p>descarga de datos - Volcado</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;tesoro de piratas - bot&iacute;n</p>\r\n<p>El terremoto de California cre&oacute; una ___ gigante en la tierra. - Grieta</p>\r\n<p>olor - Hedor</p>\r\n<p>serie numerosa de golpes dados a una persona como castigo o con la intenci&oacute;n de hacerle da&ntilde;o. - paliza</p>\r\n<p>tina; tina de manteca - Tarrina</p>\r\n<p>Dejar a una persona o un animal moment&aacute;neamente sin capacidad para actuar o comportarse de forma coordinada y normal - aturdido</p>\r\n<p>derrotar, batir crema, envolver, dar con un l&aacute;tigo - azotar</p>\r\n<p>marcar un n&uacute;mero en el aparato telef&oacute;nico - disque</p>\r\n<p>cerdo macho.&nbsp; Persona que es vulgar, porfiado y necio - verraco</p>\r\n<p>dicho o hecho tonto - bobada</p>\r\n<p>in between; involucrado; en el medio - de por medio</p>\r\n<p>agotado, muy cansado - fundido</p>\r\n<p>(lo que fuera) menester - necesario</p>\r\n<p>necesidad de una cosa - menester</p>\r\n<p>no es para menos - es logico</p>\r\n<p>lo de menos - the least (importante)</p>\r\n<p>algo que no va - inadaptados</p>\r\n<p>atribuir algo, una falta o culpa a alguien - achacar</p>\r\n<p>impaciencia, ansia, deseo, anhelo - af&aacute;n</p>\r\n<p>firme; convincente - contundente</p>\r\n<p>grueso, denso, tupido, gordo, cerrado - espeso</p>\r\n<p>agitar, sacudir, temblar, mover, menear - estremecer</p>\r\n<p>estrecho, reducido, peque&ntilde;o, restringido, corto - angosto</p>\r\n<p>plano, fluido, tranquilo, llano, blando - liso</p>\r\n<p>ben&eacute;volo, cari&ntilde;oso, benigno, favorable - bondadoso</p>\r\n<p>destruir, matar o causar da&ntilde;o de forma instant&aacute;nea - fulminar</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 42, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 18:33:09', '2019-08-15 09:01:14'),
(234, 2, 1, 3, 'Vocabulario Nuevo 3', 'vocabulario-nuevo-3', NULL, '<p><span >donde fluyo de sangre - torrente sangu&iacute;neo</span></p>\r\n<p>Lookup - apa&ntilde;arse</p>\r\n<p>casualidad (Casualidades de guerra) - baja</p>\r\n<p>pago para ayudar o aportar - subvenci&oacute;n</p>\r\n<p>moderar o suavizar - ablandar</p>\r\n<p>crueldad, atrocidad - vicisitud</p>\r\n<p>compartir las mismas ideas, sentimientos, opiniones - comulgar</p>\r\n<p>no se preocupe - no se afane</p>\r\n<p>intimidar, espantar - amedrentar</p>\r\n<p>corresponder a alguien (vamos al asunto que nos ___) - competerse</p>\r\n<p>deseo vehemente en alguien, generalmente de forma impulsiva - antojar</p>\r\n<p>es algo nuevo?&nbsp; es una ___ - novedad</p>\r\n<p>acosar con insistencia, persiguiendo, molestando, golpeando, dando l&aacute;tigo - hostigar</p>\r\n<p>cultivado, bien educado - culto</p>\r\n<p>cort&eacute;s (polite) - educado</p>\r\n<p>aceptar y cumplir una orden, ley, o regla - acatar</p>\r\n<p>revuelta o agitaci&oacute;n con la que un grupo de personas quiere mostrar su oposici&oacute;n con violencia - mot&iacute;n</p>\r\n<p>acostarse, echarse - tumbarse</p>\r\n<p>re&ntilde;ir a una persona o expresi&oacute;n de forma autoritaria a causa de su actuaci&oacute;n o su comportamiento - reprender</p>\r\n<p>animar o apoyar a una persona por lo que hace, especialmente con expresiones y gritos. - jalear</p>\r\n<p>ambos direcciones - ambos sentidos</p>\r\n<p>held accountable - rendir&aacute;n cuentas</p>\r\n<p>puesto de bebidas y comidas sencillas al aire libre, especialmente en la playa. - chiringuito</p>\r\n<p>choza, barraca o cobertizo que se construye durante las fiestas populares para vender comidas y bebidas. - chinamo</p>\r\n<p>cortar, picar, talar, desmenuzar, partir - tajar</p>\r\n<p>u&ntilde;a y carne - carne y hueso</p>\r\n<p>wield, usar, ejercer, empunar, emplear - esgrimir</p>\r\n<p>tomar una cosa por la manija, especialmente un arma. - empu&ntilde;ar</p>\r\n<p>calmante, dulce, analg&eacute;sico (soothing) - tranquilizador</p>\r\n<p>habilidad, experiencia, maestr&iacute;a, oficio - destreza</p>\r\n<p>a medida que avanzas (____ avanza en el programma) - conforme</p>', 1, 42, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:03:51', '2019-07-30 18:44:21'),
(236, 5, 40, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:21:00', '2019-07-27 20:21:00'),
(237, 5, 40, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the future tense using <strong>be going to</strong>.&nbsp; Use the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> and the simple form of the verb in parenthesis.</p>\r\n<p>I (be) going to (to hurry) because I don\'t want to miss my bus. - am</p>\r\n<p>He drank too much and now he (be) going to (to vomit). - is</p>\r\n<p>You (be) going to (to dirty) my floor with your muddy feet. - are</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:21:07', '2019-07-27 20:23:58'),
(238, 5, 40, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:24:12', '2019-07-27 20:24:12'),
(239, 5, 40, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the sentences using the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> and the simple form of the verb in parenthese to create the future tense with <strong>be going to</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ going to ___ (to assume) that he is innocent. - are</p>\r\n<p>He ___ going to ___ (to suggest) something better at the meeting. - is</p>\r\n<p>I ___ going to ___ (to give) you a sample. - am</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:24:18', '2019-07-27 20:26:33'),
(240, 5, 41, 1, 'Be Going To: Future Tense: Negative Form', 'be-going-to--future-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place not after the verb <strong>To Be</strong> to create the negative form of the future tense with <strong>be going to</strong>.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb always follows the negative form of <strong>be going to</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not going to lose.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >You are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You are not going to win.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >He is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He is not going to be there.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >She is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She is not going to eat it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >It is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It is not going to run.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >We are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We are not going to leave.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >They are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They are not going to talk.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the future tense with <strong>be going to</strong> can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.&nbsp; There is no contraction for <strong>am not</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not going to drive.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you aren\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You aren\'t going to forget.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he isn\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He isn\'t going to play.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she isn\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She isn\'t going to study.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it isn\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It isn\'t going to rain.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we aren\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We aren\'t going to try it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they aren\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They aren\'t going to like it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:27:06', '2019-07-27 20:34:15'),
(241, 5, 41, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:34:31', '2019-07-27 20:34:31'),
(242, 5, 41, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the negative form of the future tense using <strong>be going to</strong>.&nbsp; Write your answer once with <strong>am not</strong>, <strong>is not</strong>, and <strong>are not</strong> and once with <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>My company is going to annouce cutbacks for the new year. - is not going to</p>\r\n<p>My company is going to annouce cutbacks for the new year. - isn\'t going to</p>\r\n<p>We are going to submit the report in the morning. - are not going to</p>\r\n<p>We are going to submit the report in the morning. - aren\'t going to</p>\r\n<p>I am going to withdraw all of my money. - am not going to</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:34:37', '2019-07-27 20:37:28'),
(243, 5, 41, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:37:40', '2019-07-27 20:37:40'),
(244, 5, 41, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences using <strong>am not</strong> or the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong> to create the negative form of the future tense of <strong>be going to</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ going to trick you again. - aren\'t going to</p>\r\n<p>She ___ going to circle the right answer. - isn\'t going to</p>\r\n<p>I ___ going to label all the items in the store. - am not going to</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:37:46', '2019-07-27 20:39:52'),
(245, 5, 42, 1, 'Be Going To: Future Tense: Question Form', 'be-going-to--future-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place the verb to be before the subject to create questions in the future tense of <strong>be going to</strong>.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb is always used when forming questions with <strong>be going to</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >am I going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Am I going to see you?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >are you going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Are you going to visit me?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >is he going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Is he going to believe you?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >is she going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Is she going to be here?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >is it going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Is it going to start soon?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >are we going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Are we going to agree?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >are they going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Are they going to park there?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:40:31', '2019-07-27 20:43:43'),
(246, 5, 42, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:43:50', '2019-07-27 20:43:50'),
(247, 5, 42, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the question form of the future tense of <strong>be going to</strong> by placing the verb <strong>to be</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>He is going to share this knowledge with the world. - is he going to</p>\r\n<p>You are going to provide me with a good explanantion. - are you going to</p>\r\n<p>I am going to drain the vegetables with this. - Am I going to</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:43:56', '2019-07-27 20:46:15'),
(248, 5, 42, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:46:27', '2019-07-27 20:46:27'),
(249, 5, 42, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions in the future tense of <strong>be going to</strong> by placing the verb to be before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>He is going to promise to be good. - Is he going to promise to be good?</p>\r\n<p>You are going to wish for a car again. - Are you going to wish for a car again?</p>\r\n<p>I am going to compete with you. - Am I going to compete with you?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:46:33', '2019-07-27 20:48:39'),
(250, 5, 43, 1, 'The Indefinite Articles: A and An', 'the-indefinite-articles--a-and-an', NULL, '<p>The indefinite articles <strong>a</strong> and <strong>an</strong> are used with singular nouns.&nbsp; Use <strong>a</strong> before most nouns or adjectives that begin with a consonant.&nbsp; Use <strong>an</strong> before most nouns or adjectives that begin with a vowel.</p>\r\n<p>a cup</p>\r\n<p>an empty cup</p>\r\n<p>a ball</p>\r\n<p>an orange ball</p>\r\n<p>a class</p>\r\n<p>an English class</p>\r\n<p>a bug</p>\r\n<p>an ugly bug</p>\r\n<p>an egg</p>\r\n<p>a brown egg</p>\r\n<p>an idea</p>\r\n<p>a good idea</p>\r\n<p>an owl</p>\r\n<p>a white own</p>\r\n<p>an accident</p>\r\n<p>a bad accident</p>\r\n<p>Use <strong>a</strong> before nouns or adjectives that begin with a pronounced <strong>h</strong>, but use <strong>an</strong> before nouns or adjectives when the <strong>h</strong> is not pronounced.</p>\r\n<p>a house</p>\r\n<p>an honor</p>\r\n<p>a horse</p>\r\n<p>an hour</p>\r\n<p>a hammer</p>\r\n<p>an heir</p>\r\n<p>a hurricane</p>\r\n<p>an honest mistake</p>\r\n<p>Use <strong>a</strong> before nouns or adjectives if the vowel is pronounced as a consonant.&nbsp; The following words are pronounced with a <strong>y</strong> sound.</p>\r\n<p>a union</p>\r\n<p>a university</p>\r\n<p>a uniform</p>\r\n<p>a utensil</p>\r\n<p>The following words are pronounced with the <strong>w</strong> sound.</p>\r\n<p>a one-hour class</p>\r\n<p>a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:49:13', '2019-07-27 20:55:49'),
(251, 5, 43, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:56:13', '2019-07-27 20:56:13'),
(252, 5, 43, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences with <strong>a</strong> or <strong>an</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>I ate ___ orange, ___ banana, and ___ peach today. - an, a, a</p>\r\n<p>There is ___ wild ostrich in the field. - a</p>\r\n<p>I want to live on ___ island for ___ month.</p>\r\n<p>There is ___ spider, ___ ant, and ___ fly in the kitchen. - a, an, a</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:56:21', '2019-07-27 20:58:25'),
(253, 5, 43, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:58:35', '2019-07-27 20:59:26'),
(254, 5, 43, 5, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:58:41', '2019-07-27 20:59:08'),
(255, 5, 44, 1, 'Irregular Verbs Table', 'irregular-verbs-table', 'Only a big table; No exercises.', '<p>Simple / Simple Past / Past Participle</p>\r\n<p>awake / awoke / awoken</p>\r\n<p>be / was/were/ been</p>\r\n<p>beat / beat / beaten</p>\r\n<p>become / became / become</p>\r\n<p>begin / began / begun</p>\r\n<p>wake / woke / woken</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 21:00:24', '2019-07-27 21:02:23'),
(257, 5, 45, 2, 'The Present Perfect Tense, Part 2', 'the-present-perfect-tense-2', NULL, '<p>The past participle of all regular verbs is the same as the simple past tense form (add <strong>-ed</strong>).</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>INIFINITIVE</td>\r\n<td>SIMPLE PAST</td>\r\n<td>PAST PARTICIPLE</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to borrow</td>\r\n<td>borrowed</td>\r\n<td>borrowed</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to cheat</td>\r\n<td>cheated</td>\r\n<td>cheated</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to try</td>\r\n<td>tried</td>\r\n<td>tried</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to offend</td>\r\n<td>offended</td>\r\n<td>offended</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to work</td>\r\n<td>worked</td>\r\n<td>worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The part participle of all irregular verbs has a different form and must be studied and learned.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>INFINITIVE</td>\r\n<td>SIMPLE PAST</td>\r\n<td>PAST PARTICIPLE</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to grow</td>\r\n<td>grew</td>\r\n<td>grown</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to teach</td>\r\n<td>taught</td>\r\n<td>taught</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to be</td>\r\n<td>was/were</td>\r\n<td>been</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to hear</td>\r\n<td>heard</td>\r\n<td>heard</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to take</td>\r\n<td>took</td>\r\n<td>taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>It takes a lot of practice to be able to correctly use the present perfect tense.&nbsp; Learn the past participles of all the irregular verbs by heart, and you will quickly be able to use this tense proficiently.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-29 03:01:29', '2019-07-29 03:06:35'),
(258, 5, 45, 3, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the present perfect tense using has or have and the past participle of the verb in parentheses.&nbsp; Use the two preceding verb lists to complete this exercise.&nbsp; You have already learned these verbs in previous exercies.</p>\r\n<p>They (to work) in Japan. - have worked</p>\r\n<p>William (to grow) a lot since the last time I saw him. - has grown</p>\r\n<p>I (to hear) that noise in my car several times. - have heard</p>\r\n<p>We (to try) to help them. - have tried</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-29 03:06:59', '2019-07-29 03:09:45'),
(259, 5, 45, 4, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the sentences that follow to create the present perfect tense.&nbsp; Use the contracted pronoun and the past participle of the verb in parentheses.&nbsp; You have already learned these verbs in previous exercises.</p>\r\n<p>Regular</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >INFINITIVE</td>\r\n<td >SIMPLE PAST</td>\r\n<td >PAST PARTICIPLE</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >to offer</td>\r\n<td >offered</td>\r\n<td >offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >to climb</td>\r\n<td >climbed</td>\r\n<td >climbed</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >(many more...)</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Irregular</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >INFINITIVE</td>\r\n<td >SIMPLE PAST</td>\r\n<td >PAST PARTICIPLE</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >to forgive</td>\r\n<td >forgave</td>\r\n<td >forgiven</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >to bite</td>\r\n<td >bit</td>\r\n<td >biten</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >(many more...)</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>He ___ (to offer) help. - he\'s offered</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to climb) many mountains. - we\'ve climbed</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to forgive) you many times. - she\'s forgiven</p>\r\n<p>It ___ (to bite) a few people. - it\'s bitten</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-29 03:10:37', '2019-07-29 03:15:44'),
(260, 5, 46, 1, 'The Present Perfect Tense: Negative Form', 'the-present-perfect-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>not</strong> after <strong>has</strong> or <strong>have</strong> to create the negative form of the present perfect tense.&nbsp; Use the past participle of the verb in the negative form.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I have been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I have not been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I have not been to Paris.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you have been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you have not been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You have not been there.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he has been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she has not been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He has not been nice.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she has been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he has not been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She has not been happy.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it has been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it has not been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It has not been cold.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we have been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we have not been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We have not been busy.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they have been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they have not been</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They have not been on a boat.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-29 03:16:17', '2019-07-29 03:19:46'),
(261, 5, 46, 2, 'Part 2: Contactions', 'part-2--contactions', NULL, '<p>The negative form of the present perfect tense can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>hasn\'t</strong> or <strong>haven\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I have not seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I haven\'t seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I haven\'t seen it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you have not seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you haven\'t seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You haven\'t seen the play.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he has not seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he hasn\'t seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He hasn\'t seen his sister.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she has not seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she hasn\'t seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She hasn\'t seen her brother.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it has not seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it hasn\'t seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It hasn\'t seen me.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we have not seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we haven\'t seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We haven\'t seen the movie.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they have not seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they haven\'t seen</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They haven\'t seen Sara.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-29 03:20:04', '2019-07-29 03:23:30');
