(313, 11, 1, 8, 'Exercise 2', 'exercise-1', 'How to use the verb To Be.', '<p>I [am, is, are] early. - am</p>\r\n<p>The sun [am, is, are] yellow. - is</p>\r\n<p>Bob and you [am, is, are] late. - are</p>\r\n<p>The money [am, is, are] ready. - is</p>\r\n<p>We [am, is, are] the same. - are</p>\r\n<p>The flower [am, is, are] red, blue, and yellow. - is</p>\r\n<p>The store is big.&nbsp; It [am, is, are] open. - is</p>\r\n<p>I [am, is, are] different. - am</p>\r\n<p>She [am, is, are] tall and thin. - is</p>\r\n<p>The store and the restaurant [am, is, are] closed. - are</p>\r\n<p>The group is big and it [am, is, are] strong. - is</p>\r\n<p>You [am, is, are] short. - are</p>\r\n<p>The questions [am, is, are] hard. - are</p>\r\n<p>The answer [am, is, are] hard. - is</p>\r\n<p>The books [am, is, are] long. - are</p>', 1, 40, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-08-10 09:41:47', '2019-08-19 05:13:12'),
(314, 11, 1, 6, 'Exercise 1', 'exercise-2', 'How to use pronouns.', '<p>The trees are tall and [you, they, we, it] are green. - they</p>\r\n<p>The car is red and [you, he, she, it] is fast. - it</p>\r\n<p>Her eyes are open and [he, she, it, they] are blue. - they</p>\r\n<p>The cow is brown and [we, you, it, they] is hungry. - it</p>\r\n<p>[I, You, We, They] am tired. - I</p>\r\n<p>[I, It, She, You] are tall. - you</p>\r\n<p>The man is young and [we, you, he, she] is strong. - he</p>\r\n<p>You and I are awake and [you, I, they, we] are tired. - we</p>\r\n<p>Mary is young and [she, he, it, we] is smart. - she</p>\r\n<p>Jane, you, and I are tall and [we, they, you, I] are thin. - we</p>', 1, 40, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-08-10 20:44:36', '2019-10-14 17:09:00'),
(315, 2, 5, 9, 'ir + gerundio', 'ir---gerundio', NULL, '<p>El gerundio con ir espesa poco a poco, gradualmente&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Voy haciendolo.</p>\r\n<p>Ella va aprendiendo el ingl&eacute;s.</p>\r\n<p>Vamos construyendo la casa.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-08-12 01:07:53', '2019-08-12 01:12:11'),
(316, 2, 2, 1, '10 Frases para demostrar todo', '10-frases-para-demostrar-todo', NULL, '<p>Si hubiera tenido m&aacute;s tiempo, lo _______ hecho yo mismo. - habr&iacute;a</p>\r\n<p>Se lo expliqu&eacute; cuidadosamente para que ella se _______ (dar) cuenta de lo importante que era. - diera</p>\r\n<p>_______ (nos. could) haber ido a la playa pero estaba lloviendo. - Podr&iacute;amos</p>\r\n<p>_______ (nos. should) haber ido a la playa pero estaba lloviendo. - Deber&iacute;amos</p>\r\n<p>_______ (nos. would) ido a la playa pero estaba lloviendo. - Habr&iacute;amos</p>\r\n<p>_____ _____ (would be) un acontecimiento aparatoso de la temporada, pero no acontec&iacute;o. - Hubiera sido</p>\r\n<p>Por la pr&oacute;xima semana (nos.) _______ ahorrado todo el dinero. - habremos</p>\r\n<p>Llegaremos antes de que ellos se _______ ido. - hayan</p>\r\n<p>El discurso contundente los dej&oacute; aturdidos porque su (eagerness, desire) _______ no era para menos. - af&aacute;n</p>\r\n<p>Me encargar&eacute; del dinero _____ _____ _____ (con tal de) que no los hostigue m&aacute;s. - siempre y cuando</p>\r\n<p>Antes de que sucediera, quer&iacute;a que _______ (t&uacute; saber). - supieras</p>\r\n<p>_____ _____ que (were supposed to) ibamos a llegar temprano - se supon&iacute;a</p>\r\n<p>_____ _____ que (are supposed to) llegar temprano - se supone</p>', 1, 30, 0, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2019-08-13 21:01:22', '2019-08-15 01:23:13');
